title: dry hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container or it will harden.
Mix 1/4 cup of mix with hot water.
Add more Quik to taste, if desired.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese and beat until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in a cold oven and set temperature at 325°.
Bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 15 minutes in pan before removing.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Stir flour mixture into banana mixture; batter will be slightly lumpy.

title: molasses no bake squares(from spain)
directions: Combine molasses, vanilla pudding mix, butter and cream in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat.
When mix comes to a boil, remove. Add Rice Krispies and walnuts.
Combine lightly, but thoroughly. Press into buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut into squares. Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: low-fat crab dip
directions: Cream the salad dressing and cream cheese together.
Add the remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve on fat-free crackers. Yields 2 cups; 16 (1/8 cup) servings.

title: lime chiffon dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of an 8-inch square or 11 x 7-inch glass dish.
Chill.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Chop crookneck and zucchini and heat with spaghetti sauce.
Mix Ricotta, eggs or egg whites, approximately 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese, approximately 2 cups of chopped spinach and Italian seasoning to taste.
Drain the lasagna, then spread some of the Ricotta mixture on top; roll lasagna like a pinwheel.
Place roll-ups in a large pan with high sides and when all have been completed, pour spaghetti sauce with squash on top of roll-ups.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top; bake at 350° until cheese starts to bubble.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar, apples and pecans. Beat by hand. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well by hand.
Bake in an ungreased food cake pan (Bundt) for 60 minutes at 350°. Serve with softened cream cheese.

title: chilled corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: french bread with biloxi butter
directions: Cream butter and garlic until light and fluffy.
Fold shrimp into butter and mix well.
Serve on hot French bread.
May also be toasted under broiler.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in oven.
Add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Put in square pan or dish. Lay Hershey bars on top.
Melt in oven.
Refrigerate until all gone!

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Remove stem and core.
Cut into thin slices. Cook tomatoes in water until tender.
Add sugar, salt and butter. Mix clear jel with cold water.
Add to hot tomato mixture. Continue cooking until it thickens.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Add top sheet of dough.
Seal and make edges.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes.

title: spiced cider
directions: Add all ingredients to basket of 30 cup coffee pot.
Perk 10 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oil, lime juice, salt, garlic and red pepper; mix well.
Add chicken; toss to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Place chicken on a rack in a broiler pan.
Broil under a preheated hot broiler until no longer pink in the center, turning once.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Combine the carrots, sour cream and soup in another bowl.
Mix the butter and dressing together.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 dressing mixture. Drain squash well and mix with soup mixture.
Place on dressing. Top with remaining dressing and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or brown.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Toss all vegetables and spread on cheese mixture.
Sprinkle on 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese. Cover with Saran Wrap and press vegetables.
Chill, then eat.

title: easy burrito casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain and rinse beef and return to skillet.
Add soup, salsa and seasonings.
Stir and simmer until thoroughly mixed.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix and beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Dip sliced apples into dip. Tart apples are best.
Rinse apples in salt water or lemon juice to keep apples white.

title: cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Cut slice from top of bread.
Remove center, leaving 1-inch shell. Cut removed bread into bite size pieces; save.
Brush sides of shell with 3 tablespoons melted margarine. Place on cookie sheet, along with saved bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended. Fold in nuts last.
Put into five medium sized greased foil bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: puffed pancake
directions: Put a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or a large cast-iron skillet into the oven and heat oven to 425°.
Meanwhile, process eggs, milk, juice, sugar, flour and salt in blender or food processor until well blended.
Add butter to hot pan and heat 1 to 2 minutes until butter sizzles (check often so it doesn't get brown).
Holding hot pan with pot holders, tip to coat bottom with butter. Immediately pour in batter.
Bake about 20 minutes until puffed and brown. Dust with confectioners sugar and serve with toppings. Yields 6 servings at 312 calories each.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend and mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: pancakes
directions: Add the ingredients in the order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Fry and serve with warm maple syrup.
(Makes about 2 dozen medium-sized pancakes.)

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 375° for 1 hour or until tender. Let cool. Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato and discard. Scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell. In a bowl, mash the pulp with butter. Stir in milk, bacon, cup of cheese, chives, salt and pepper. Spoon into potato shells. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: soup clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onions.
Add clam juice, water and potatoes. Boil until tender.
Stir flour into 1/2 cup milk until smooth. Add to chowder, stirring until thick.
Stir in remaining milk, clams, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.

title: no crust zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: eva's fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add ingredients. Pour 1/2 in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Cool in refrigerator (leave other 1/2 out so it will not congeal).
Cover congealed 1/2 with sour cream.
Pour rest of strawberry mix.
Refrigerate.

title: cooked play dough
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine dry ingredients; stir in oil, water and food coloring.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture pulls away from pan.
Turn out onto waxed-paper-covered counter or tabletop (to avoid staining surface) and knead until smooth.
The dough will keep up to a couple of weeks in an airtight container and does not require refrigeration. For texture variations, add dry coffee grounds, sand, glitter and dry Jell-O.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Shake biscuit pieces in bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuit pieces in bottom of a solid tube pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans between layers.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Boil 1 minute; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and then turn out of pan.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix together the jello, hot water, pie filling and pineapple; let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice, butter and salt in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool, then mix with cherries, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream; spoon gently into serving bowl.
Cover; chill for 24 hours in the refrigerator.
One-half to 2 cups of Cool Whip may be used instead of whipped cream.

title: cheese strata
directions: Oil a 13 x 9 inch casserole or baking dish.
Using a biscuit cutter, cut circles out of the bread slices.
Set the circles aside for the top of the casserole and fit the scraps of bread into the prepared dish.
Cover the bread scraps with cheese slices, and sprinkle with ham. Arrange the bread circles on top. Beat the eggs in a mixing bowl.
Whisk in the milk, salt, butter, mustard and onion.
Pour over the casserole, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, milk and cocoa.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Cook meatballs.
Drain fat from skillet and remove meatballs. Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup), vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: All ingredients at room temperature. Mix with hands and press in pan. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and loosen with fork. Cool slightly. Press flat in pan. When cool, add filling.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings in bowl; mix well.
Place chicken halves on grill over medium coals; brush with sauce.
Grill for one hour or until chickens are tender, turning and basting frequently.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit punch(for 25)
directions: Boil the sugar and the first amount of water listed.
Cool. Cut up the fruit; combine all the ingredients.
Serve as cold as possible.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Press 8 rolls for crust in pie pan. Mix other ingredients; pour into crust. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer about 2 to 3 hours on low heat. Makes 3/4 gallon.

title: meat macaroni supper
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter.
Cook chopped onion in the butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in cream of celery soup, tomatoes, thyme and dash of pepper.
Add macaroni, luncheon meat and green pepper. Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with shredded cheese.
Then bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes. It will serve 4 to 6.

title: mom's fried cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage finely.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add cabbage; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper; simmer 10 minutes, or until sausages are done.

title: hot chocolate mix(the camper's favorite)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Put in a large, airtight container.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place. Use within 6 months.
Makes about 17 cups of Hot Chocolate Mix.

title: catfish stew
directions: Put 3 slices bacon in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and cover bacon with some of the potatoes.
Now slice catfish and put on top.
Do this until dish is almost filled.
Now pour half cup of catsup, mixed with 1/4 cup of water.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn in large amount of boiling water for 5 minutes. Plunge in cold water.
Drain.
Cut corn from cobs.
Do not scrape cobs.
Measure 8 cups corn.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and dip boiled wieners into it.
Drop into hot fat until brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread ground beef in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Drain off grease.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water and cover casserole. Layer Tater Tots and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until browned.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Heat chocolate chips over hot water; add beaten egg yolks. Whip egg whites with dab of salt.
Add sugar.
Add chocolate and egg yolk mixture to whites.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break cake up into small pieces.
Put layer of cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour 1/2 of chocolate mixture over cake.
Repeat layers.
Chill. Dessert is better if it sits in refrigerator overnight.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, pressing edges to line bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool. Combine cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix and beat until smooth.
Spread over crust. Combine vegetables and cheese and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture. Cover and chill 8 hours. Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain water off corn and green beans.
Mix corn, green beans, soup, sour cream and cheese in a large bowl.
Be sure to mix well. Pour mixture in a casserole dish.
Crumble crackers into fine crumbs.
If you don't have a food processor, a blender works great (or your hands).
Spread crumbs on top of casserole.
Pour melted butter on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until it shakes like jello and is warm throughout, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese and cover with potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Pinch angel food cake up in small pieces, put in bottom of bowl.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Spread over top of cake.
Mix glaze and strawberries together.
Spread over top.
Chill.

title: old fashioned salt brine pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in sterilized jars.
Boil the vinegar, water and salt together in a large pot.
Pour the hot liquid over the cucumbers.
Seal and put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the ingredients and press into an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish; bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pumpkin, then the milk.
Pour into an unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted into filling comes out clean.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Will be moist.
Cool cake, then frost with icing.

title: lemon squares(prepared the day before)
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture holds together.
Pat evenly into an ungreased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs; add brown sugar, coconut, baking powder and vanilla extract.
Spread over baked base.
Return to oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Actually, about 28 minutes is right.)
Blend together powdered sugar, lemon rinds and lemon juice.
Frost cookies while they are very hot, immediately on removing from the oven.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Leave uncovered, at least overnight, before storing in airtight container.
Yields about 24.

title: pasticchio
directions: Brown hamburg with salt.
Drain grease.
Add 1 stick of butter, cinnamon, cooked macaroni and 8 ounces cheese.
Heat milk with 1 stick of butter.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and remaining cheese.
Mix with other mixtures.
Spread in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: vegetable or chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 12 hours before serving.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Crush crackers into crumbs. Fold crumbs and remaining ingredients into beaten egg whites. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Be sure to grease pie plate well. After it cools, cover with whipped cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in the carrots, pineapple and walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter.
Boil and add pineapple.
Cook about 25 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Cool; add lemon juice and beat until sugar begins.
Pour into tins and make squares.

title: roasted sausage on buns
directions: Grind sausage, eggs and onion together.
Mix with cheese and soup.
Put on split buns.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate 1/3 hour. Bake at 275° until hot.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt
butter and mix all ingredients.
Bake in pie shell for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix dates, baking soda and boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk, salt and vanilla.
Add date mixture alternately with flour to sugar, egg mixture.
Add nuts. Beat egg white stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in loaf pan 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: chicken with spicy fruit sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large non-aluminum skillet; bring to a boil.
Add chicken; cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Bring cooking liquid to a boil; cook 7 minutes or until reduced to 3/4 cup, stirring occasionally.
Combine strawberry spread and cornstarch; stir into cooking liquid and cook 1 minute or until syrupy.
Spoon 3 tablespoons sauce over each chicken breast; garnish with green onion strips, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings (about 215 calories per serving).
Protein 26.9; Fat 1.5; Carb. 22.7; Choles. 66; Iron 1.2; Sodium 77; Calcium 34.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 1-quart water and sugar one minute.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve in a punch bowl with ice cubes.
Garnish with orange or lemon slices and with sprigs of mint.
Orange sherbet may be added to the punch for ice; in that case, cut down on orange juice in recipe.
Serves 50.

title: grape salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, combine jello and boiling water.
Add blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator overnight and then top with cream cheese, sugar and sour cream. Cream the cream cheese and sugar and fold sour cream in gently. Do not use mixer.

title: hot cheesy salsa dip
directions: Combine the cheese spread, cream cheese, salsa and ripe olives in a 1 qt. microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 2 minutes and stir. Microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes longer or until the dip is bubbly around the edge and the cheese is melted when stirred. Serve with homemade tortilla chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic and pepper; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then in cheese mixture.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish. Drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix oleo, egg, water and coconut with cake mix.
Put dough into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden (crust is still soft when done).
Prepare lemon pie filling mix; pour over cooled crust.
Chill.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp.
Put shrimp peels, onion skins and tops in a stock pot.
Cover with water and boil for 20 minutes.
Strain and reserve broth.
Make a dark roux with the flour and oil.
Add onion and allow to caramelize.
Add celery and bell pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes, then add the crabs, tomatoes, herbs, okra and the shrimp broth.
Add garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 45 minutes or longer.
Ten minutes before serving, add shrimp and green onions.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Then add oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water.
Mix until smooth batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Repeat two times.
Mix well.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Put ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Rinse and drain wild rice.
In large skillet, cook and stir almonds in butter until almonds are golden.
Pour wild rice into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat broth to boiling.
Stir into wild rice.
Stir in almonds, onions and mushrooms.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar and blend well.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: polynesian butterscotch cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, salt and soda.
In large bowl, beat oleo, oil, sugars and egg until creamy.
Slowly add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until edges are crisp and centers are soft. You don't need to grease the pan, but I spray my pans.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus in baking dish.
Add chopped almonds, mashed eggs, mushroom soup, grated cheese and corn.
Pour melted butter over this and bake 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Melt butter and add beef and onion, brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and put into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lima beans and cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in fourths and boil in salted water to cover.
In another pot, put beans, cream, butter and a little salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then add cornstarch which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup water. Cook until smooth.
Place a layer of cabbage, then a layer of bean mixture into casserole dish until it is full.
Cover top of dish with bread cubes and bake until bread is brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water and drain.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight and stir next day before serving.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks; stir occasionally.
Very good with soup.

title: bake taters
directions: Cut baking potatoes in quarters.
Mix well and roll quartered potatoes in mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over them.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Put in muffin pan (1/2 full).
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: sorrel
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over sorrel and ginger.
Steep for 4 hours.
Sweeten to taste with sugar or honey.
Serve chilled.

title: cranberry swirl coffeecake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, sour cream and flavoring, mixing quickly and thoroughly.

title: deluxe baked beans
directions: Brown beef and 4 slices bacon.
Crumble bacon.
Put all ingredients into baking dish and mix together.
Put remaining bacon on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: In a 9-inch pan with crust, line peaches in bottom of pan. Cream together sugar, butter, flour, egg and milk.
Spread over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and roll into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender and drain.
Layer carrots, peppers and onion in a shallow dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover tightly and marinate for 12 hours.
Drain partially to serve.

title: aunt carolyn's wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in oblong pan.
Make 3 wells.
Mix oil, vinegar and vanilla, then pour into wells.
Pour water over all and mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Place oil into iron skillet.
Add rice and brown, stirring constantly.
When rice gets dark brown, remove skillet from burner and add water.
Reduce heat of burner to lowest setting.
Return skillet to burner and cook, tightly covered, for about 15 minutes.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut the softened margarine into the dry cake mix.
Put this mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Build up the edges slightly.
Bake this for 10 minutes at 350°.
Drain most of the juice from the canned apples.
Arrange the slices over the top of the partially cooled baked crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top of apples.
Combine sour cream and beaten egg. Drizzle over top of apples and sugar.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° until edges are light brown.
Do not over bake.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Place peaches in pan.
Mix sugar, Bisquick and milk and pour over peaches.
Dot with tablespoon of butter.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: fried egg rolls
directions: Mix rice wine, 1/3 teaspoon salt and cornstarch with pork loin; heat pan and 4 tablespoons oil.
Stir-fry pork shreds until color changes; remove and drain.
Blanch bean sprouts, carrots and Chinese chives in boiling water; plunge into cold water to cool and drain.
In a bowl, mix pork shreds, carrot shreds, bean sprouts and Chinese chives; add 1 tablespoon salt, m.s.g., sugar, black pepper and sesame oil and toss lightly; separate into 16 equal portions.
Moisten a 1/2-inch band around the edge of the top half of the skin with flour and water; place a portion of filling in the middle of each skin; wrap filling up like
a package in egg roll skins.
Rolls should be about 4-inches long. Heat oil for deep frying egg rolls over medium heat for 4 minutes until golden brown; remove and drain.

title: chicken broccoli braid
directions: Mix in order listed. Then spread rolls out in a square. Press the rolls together to connect forming a rectangle. Take mixture and place in the center all the way down leaving room along the edge to cut slits in the rolls. Cut slits on both sides of the rolls then roll the cut roll up over the mixture on both sides as to braid. Spread the braid with melted butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed beef bracholi
directions: Saute steak, onion, green pepper, red pepper and mushrooms in a little oil, then add salt and thyme.
Saute bacon; cut up and drain well.
Add to first mixture.
Next, add bread crumbs, spinach and apple and spread mustard of your choice on meat.
Put filling on long side of meat.
Lay spinach leaves on top of filling.
Last, put sliced apples on top of spinach leaves.
Roll as jelly roll and tie with string.
Bake in pan sprayed with Pam at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Heat juices and water to boiling.
Pour over jello; stir.
Add cheese and marshmallows to hot mixture.
Cool.
Add pineapple and orange sections.
Place in refrigerator.
When it becomes thick, fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until firm in the center.

title: hog's head cheese
directions: Put all ingredients except parsley and green onions in a large heavy pot.
Cover with water until about one inch over meat. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low simmer.
Cook 3 to 4 hours. Strain out meat.
Add green onions and parsley to liquid. Carefully remove all bone from feet and hocks.
Chop meat, but not too finely.
Add back to liquid.
Taste for seasoning.
When hot it should taste a little over salty and peppery.
Pour into any size pan (best if it is 2 inches deep) and let cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
If needs more salt or pepper, can be melted and repoured.

title: gift wrapped chicken
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half the short way and pound. Place 1 tablespoon cranberry sauce and 1 tablespoon butter on each half breast.
Put two halves together with filling in middle.
Cut dough in half the long way.
Brush 4 pieces with melted butter. Stack 2 strips to make an "X" and 2 strips on top of that making a "+".
Put filled chicken breast in center and pinch all ends together on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, flavorings and flour.
Spread evenly in a large jelly roll pan and score into 24 squares.
Drop 2 to 3 cherries from pie filling onto each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy stuffing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato-dill soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in onion and cook about 2 minutes until soft.
Stir in potatoes and cook about 2 minutes, but do not brown.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cover pan and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes, leaving some small pieces.
Add chicken bouillon, milk and dill and bring to a boil.
Stir flour into sour cream and blend into soup with spoon or wire whisk.
Remove soup from heat and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut cooked chicken up in casserole bowl.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and eggs.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers on top.
Slice butter over crackers. Cook at 325° until bubbles, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken stock adding sufficient water to make the quantity of liquid required for the directions on noodle package.

title: southern casserole
directions: Place sliced vegetables in frying pan with water.
Cut up sausage on top.
Bring to boil, then cut down to low heat.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: pecan dip spread
directions: Combine cheese and milk.
Mix well; stir in dried beef, onion and seasonings.
Mix well, fold in sour cream and spoon into a lightly greased pie plate or shallow dish.
Sprinkle pecans over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: tortellini italian style(yields 8 servings)
directions: Will also need a 3-quart baking dish or pan.

title: grandmoo's chicken soup(dumdum version)
directions: Earlier in the day, rinse all meat.
Double the recipe if using whole chicken/parts.
Peel carrots, celery and parsnip. Wash leek well.
Dip onion in a little salt.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix 1/3 cup Pet milk, cake mix, pecans and butter.
Take 1/2 of mixture and pat it on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased). Cook at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: good meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake at 375° until done.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Good with fresh vegetables.

title: pineapple nut cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir flour with sugar, soda, salt, pineapple, eggs, vanilla and nuts until well mixed.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients - mixing well and chill thoroughly. Shape and coat with pecans (chopped very fine).
Yields about ten servings.

title: roman beef stew
directions: Cooking Time: About 1 1/2 hours.
Servings: 6.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli and season with Beau Monde.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix corn, egg, cracker crumbs and onions. Pour over broccoli and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc., just as long as you have a pan big enough to cook it in.
Increase baking time when making additional recipes.

title: iced coffee
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and blend.
Pour into a glass over ice.

title: dolle's caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except popcorn and cook until reaches 290°, measuring with a candy thermometer.
When the mixture reaches 290°, pour over the popcorn while popcorn is spread out on a cookie sheet.
Add 2 more tablespoons of butter and mix the popcorn and ingredients together while on cookie sheet.
Let stand to cool and store in airtight tin.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts of caramel popcorn.
Shelf life should be 2 to 3 weeks.

title: easy individual trifles
directions: Split ladyfingers in half lengthwise.
Spread 1 teaspoon of raspberry jam on bottom half of each ladyfinger.
Arrange, crosswise, 4 filled halves in each individual serving dish. Drizzle each with 1 teaspoon sherry and 1 teaspoon orange juice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar, oranges, salt and soda; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Let cheese and butter soften; stir in flour and blend well. Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape into small balls and place each in miniature muffin tins.
Press into shape bottom and sides.

title: clam casserole
directions: Melt butter in a casserole.
Combine clams, juice, dill weed, saltines and beaten eggs with milk.
Add pepper and paprika.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 9.
Enjoy.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking pan. Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.
Yields 48 pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In
a bowl, place flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Toss
lightly
with
a fork to mix.
In a large bowl,
beat
eggs
well.
Gradually
add
sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add
vanilla
and
dry
ingredients.
Stir
well.
Add zucchini and
nuts.
Spread batter in well buttered 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake
in
a 350° oven for 80 to 90 minutes or until done (or use 2 buttered 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans and cook 60 minutes).
Recipe
can
be
used for muffins.
Makes 18 muffins. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water until dissolved. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Chill until slightly thickened. Pour in mold and chill thoroughly.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in.
Add flavoring.
Bake in large, greased and well floured tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until really frothy.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating until thick and creamy.
Add next 4 ingredients, then add apples or Comstock apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook red beans in slow cooker until mostly done.
Add ham, sausage, onions and peppers and continue cooking until beans are beginning to mush.
Pour over cooked rice.
May garnish with hot sauce, if desired.

title: brunch egg casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix eggs,
milk
and salt.
Butter both sides of bread. Dip bread in egg
mixture.
Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish with
spaces
between
edges
of bread (6 slices).	Layer cheese on top.
Break up remaining bread into small pieces and scatter over cheese mix.
Pour remaining egg mixture on top of casserole. Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions and drain. Rinse with cold water and drain well. In a large mixing bowl, combine cooked tortellini, sweet pepper, broccoli, carrot and olives.

title: chamber chutney cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften out of the refrigerator.
Mix in chutney, onion and chives.
Form cheese into a ball on a small plate and refrigerate until firm.
Push walnuts into cheese to cover whole ball.
Serve with Triscuits or other cracker.

title: shrimp sea island
directions: Clean shrimp, wash and drain.
In a deep, flat dish, place a layer of shrimp and then a layer of sliced onions, alternating until all ingredients are used.
Mix oil, vinegar and caper dressing thoroughly and pour over shrimp and onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving, stirring at intervals.
Serve on a large platter decorated with crisp lettuce leaves and parsley.
A fine buffet dish - or a great shrimp salad!

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Cook zucchini until tender-crisp.
Add lemon juice and salt. Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add zucchini; mix well.
It will be runny, but okay.
Dump filling into 9-inch crust.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: debbie's cheesy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes; add to water.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until done; drain.
Combine 6 cups water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and olive oil.
Bring to a boil and add spaghetti; cook 10 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain well and set aside.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 12-cup muffin pan.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, oil, honey and vanilla.
In a large bowl, combine flour, bran, baking powder and baking soda.
Add eggs, oil, honey and vanilla mixture and stir until mixed.
Blend in blueberries.
Pour batter into buttered muffin pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chopped celery, pepper and onion.
Melt cheese and add taco sauce.
Cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Roll Fritos until just barely broken.
Add hamburger mixture.
Add cheese mixture and mix.
Top with black olives and sour cream, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Place potatoes in a greased baking dish; cover with cheese sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pink frozen arctic salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with mayonnaise, sugar, cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip.
Place in lined muffin tins and freeze.
Remove and place in freezer bags and keep frozen until ready to serve.
Top with dollop of whipped cream.
(Do not use Cool Whip or Miracle Whip salad dressing.)

title: crisp cinnamon jumbles(pre-civil war family recipe)
directions: Mix well.
Roll very thin; sprinkle with granulated sugar and roll lightly.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters or knife and insert halves of blanched almonds after cookies have been placed on cookie sheets.
Cook in 375° oven for approximately 8 minutes, until edges begin to brown.
(Makes approximately 150 two-inch stars.)

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: This makes 3 coffee cakes or about 60 rolls.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Dissolve sugar, shortening and salt in boiling water in small saucepan.
When cool, pour into large bowl.
Add yeast, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer until frothy.
Add 3 more cups of flour; mix well.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until needed.
Will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine fresh vegetables and chicken.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes in jar.
Make a brine of 1/2 cup vinegar, plus 2 tablespoons salt for each cup of water.
Boil the brine for approximately 2 minutes.
Pour over tomatoes and seal jars.
Use in 1 month.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mint roasted onions
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan with foil.
Cut onions in half crosswise.
Remove skins. Place, cut side down, in pan.
Whisk remaining ingredients in small bowl until blended. Drizzle over onions. Swirl onions so they are coated.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until tender and golden brown. Baste onions with pan drippings 3 times during baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peppy deviled eggs
directions: Remove shells from eggs and halve lengthwise.
Carefully remove yolks and place in small bowl.
Add mustard, salt, pepper, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 24 deviled eggs.

title: easy baked stuffed scallop casserole
directions: Cooking Time: 30 to 35 minutes.
Servings: 4 to 5.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Chop parsley, green onions, celery and green pepper.
Make a roux of the 1 stick of oleo and 8 tablespoons of flour.
(Takes about 30 to 45 minutes,)
Add chopped vegetables and garlic powder to roux and saute for about 10 to 15 minutes, then add water, tomato paste, salt, sugar, red pepper, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then add the vinegar.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves about 25 people.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Drain your vegetables and tuna fish. Add the soup. Mix together and pour into the bottom pie crust. You can add sliced or shredded cheese on top prior to top crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Put pie crusts on cookie sheet.
Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake in 325° oven until knife comes out clean from center of pie.

title: old fashion soup
directions: Slowly boil beef in large pot.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Cook until tender (2 to 3 hours).
Remove meat and set aside.

title: holiday ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package. Drain.
Spread in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana pulp; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated, moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour. Cool well; store overnight before cutting.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Line bottom of dish with hash brown patties.
Bake 5 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Brown ground beef.
Season with onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef to hash browns.
Top with mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Add sliced tomatoes and boiled broccoli.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: potato soup
directions: Place prepared vegetables in a big kettle and add enough water to completely cover.
Cook until tender and remove from heat.
Make up flour thickening by mixing flour with about a 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid to form a paste.
Slowly stir this into the rest of the soup and heat to thicken, stirring constantly.
Then add butter, salt and pepper.
Add the evaporated milk and continue to heat over a very low fire.
Stir to keep from burning.
Enjoy!
The evaporated milk makes it very good.

title: apple walnut upside-down pie
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar; beat to combine.
Spread butter-sugar mixture in the bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over butter-sugar mixture.
Divide pie pastry in half; roll each half to 1/8 inch thick.
Carefully line prepared pie pan with dough so as not to make holes in dough with nuts. Trim even with edge of the pan.
Fill pan with cubed apples.

title: pea salad
directions: Add a little cheese, chopped.
Touch of salt, sugar and pepper. Bacon bits on top, if desired.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt; add onion and put in dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top, if desired.
Bake at 325° until set, but moist, about 35 minutes.

title: honey almond squares
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Cream the cheese and gradually add honey; beat until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the pecans.
Sprinkle with red pepper to taste.
After mixing, roll into a ball or into a log, then roll in chopped nuts, covering the whole piece.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Crush cracker and mix with melted margarine.
Put 1/2 of that mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together and put on top of cracker-margarine mixture.
Top with other 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Marinate shelled, deveined shrimp in mixture of ingredients. Preheat broiler to 500°.
Put shrimp in marinade in broiler pan 4-inches from heat.
Broil 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Broil about 5 more minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix with hands and roll into bite size balls.
Melt 1/4 bar paraffin with 1 (6 ounce) bag chocolate morsels.
Dip balls into heated mixture and place on wax paper.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Whip egg white and water until frothy.
Coat nut meats.
Blend sugar and spices.
Toss and mix with nuts (a bag is handy).
Spread on large baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Shake off loose coating.
Crispy, not too sweet.

title: olive appetizers
directions: Cream butter and cheese until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except olives and mix well.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes. Shape a small portion of dough around each olive.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) about 15 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: pork chop abracadabra
directions: Brown pork chops well and season lightly with salt and pepper. Place in crock-pot and cook on low 7 to 9 hours.
Use any sauce for a special treat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take meat from the bones.
Put in the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and milk.
Pour this mixture over the chicken.
Melt the oleo. Crush the Ritz crackers and mix well with oleo.
Put over the mixture in the dish. Sprinkle poppy seed over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar together in a buttered casserole.
Mix oats, brown sugar, butter and flour.
Pat on top of apples and cranberries.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake loaf 1 hour at 300°.
Bundt pan suggested.

title: russian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, dice and marinate in dressing until cool.
Mix with other diced ingredients.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and cool.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Stir well by hand (batter will be thick).
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raspberry cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and juice.
Mix well; add nuts and chill until set.

title: chocolate caramel delight
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as normal and divide in two.
Take 1/2 of mix and pour in pan and bake for 15 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt caramels, milk and butter. Pour mixture over bottom layer of cake, then top with other half of cake mix and finish baking cake.
Cool and ice with fudge icing.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thick, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add soup, water, soy sauce and rice.
Mix and put in a casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Put chow mein noodles over top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Place cake mix, butter, instant pudding, sour cream, vanilla, oil and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Divide mixture in half.
Add chocolate chips to one mixture and the chocolate syrup to the other mixture.
Alternate batters in Bundt pan. Swirl with a knife. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
No frosting is necessary as this cake is real rich.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Remove and brown rice in same pan.
Then add onion and bell pepper and bouillon.
Bake covered at 325° for 45 minutes.
Good with any kind of wild game.

title: trailside cookies
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter and sugars until creamy. Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in oats, chocolate pieces and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crispix mix
directions: Boil margarine, corn syrup and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over cereal mix. Divide into 2 pans.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator while still hot.

title: snuggled hot dogs
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; beat well.
Spread into a 9 x 5-inch greased baking pan.
Partially split hot dogs.
Fill split with 6 strips of cheese or 2 tablespoons relish or catsup. Arrange hot dogs crosswise on dough in pan.
Press lightly.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: colorado peach cream pie
directions: To make crust, cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Press dough into 9 inch pie pan.
For filling, slice peaches into a bowl and sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the sugar. Let stand while preparing the rest of the filling.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour, egg, 1/4 tsp. salt and vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Stir into peaches and pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
After 15 minutes, reset oven to 350° and bake another 20 minutes.
For topping, combine 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, 1/4 cup butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
After pie has baked for 20 minutes at 350°, sprinkle the crumbs over the top of the pie.
Then bake another 10 minutes at 400° until lightly brown.

title: jiffy baked fish
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Dip into milk.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over fish.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Approximately 5 servings per pound.
Use orange roughy or any white fish.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: In bowl, add all ingredients, mixing well.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Leave, covered, until last 15 minutes.

title: down-home dumplings
directions: Bring margarine and milk to a boil; blend flour and salt and add all at once to milk mixture on heat.
Stir vigorously until dough loosens from sides of pan.
Remove
from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Bring broth to a boil.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into boiling broth.
Cook on low heat 15 minutes or until dumplings float to top.

title: crab and shrimp dip for chafing dish
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mushroom soup, lime juice, mayonnaise, red hot, paprika, pepper and salt.
Heat until warm. When ready to serve, fold in chopped onion, parsley, shrimp and crab meat.
Serve hot from chafing dish with Triscuits, Wheat Thins, etc.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Place chops in roasting pan. Mix other ingredients and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix well.
Cook in an iron skillet or 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir often.
After mixture starts to boil, cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Eat over buttered biscuits and enjoy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Combine sugar and peanut butter and add to cheese.
Slowly stir in 1/2 cup milk. Fold in Cool Whip, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into crust. Freeze until firm and set.
Cut frozen.
Top with chocolate syrup, Cool Whip or nuts.

title: tasty chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in a large bowl with tight fitting lid.
Stir until sugar has dissolved.
Add chicken to marinade.
Let soak for 3 days, rotating chicken daily.
Remove and grill, fry in oil or bake.

title: salsa pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium-low heat, combine salsa, ricotta, olives and garlic.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes until heated through. Spoon sauce over hot pasta.
Sprinkle with walnuts, cilantro and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan in 325° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Halfway through baking, remove from oven and shake pan to make waxy.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Place steak strips, scallions and broth into 2 1/2 quart microwave-safe dish.
Cook 3 minutes, stir in cornstarch.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir twice and fluff with fork.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and Cool Whip; mix.
Add pineapple; mix.
Add dry jello.
Use strawberries and pecans if desired.

title: our favorite apple cake
directions: Instead of apples, fresh peach slices can be used or 1/2 cut pieces of plums.

title: wild rice and country ham tart
directions: Bake pie crust at 425° until golden brown.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over crust.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour over cheese.
Beat together eggs, sour cream, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over ham.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese log
directions: Let cheeses set at room temperature.
Form in log after adding pecans and garlic powder.
Roll in chili powder.

title: blueberry cottage pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 7 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; turn into prepared pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Combine milk, butter and remaining egg.
Add to dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Spoon over berries up to edge.
Bake until tester inserted comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Boil fryer in 3 quarts water to which 1 bay leaf, dried thyme leaves, salt and chicken bouillon have been added.	Cook until done and cool in liquid.
Skin
and
bone
chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
(This may be	done ahead and stored in refrigerator.) Save broth.

title: tarragon chicken with asparagus
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in lemon and tarragon for 2 hours or overnight.
Stem asparagus.
Set aside.
Place wine in frying pan and bring to a boil.
Remove chicken from marinade and poach in wine until tender, 3 minutes each side.
Garnish chicken with 2 crossed asparagus and 2 shrimp with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and wash.
Put into kettle to boil.
Add water to apples until it covers about 1/2 of the apples.
Boil until apples are soft and mushy.
Stir often so it doesn't scorch on the bottom of the kettle.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Some apples are sweeter than others, so you will have to taste for sweetness.

title: bean relish
directions: Drain beans, reserve liquid.
Mix reserved liquid with vinegar, sugar, dill seed, pickling spices and 1 teaspoon salt; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans; heat through.
Cool and drain.
Toss with onion and oil. Cover and chill overnight.
This will keep up to a week in a tightly covered plastic container.

title: mom's pineapple pie
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan (except egg yolk, vanilla, pie crust and whipped cream).
Stir on low heat until boils.
Stir constantly so it doesn't burn.
After boils, add beaten egg yolk, cook 1 minute longer.
Add vanilla.
It should appear thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour and top with whipped cream.

title: cheezy onion potato casserole
directions: Slice onions and potatoes; cook until tender.
Drain onions and potatoes.
Mix cheese soup and water; cook over medium heat until blended.
Layer potatoes and cheese soup, starting with potatoes in a buttered or Pam coated baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Place slices of cheese on top before baking.
Cook until cheese begins to turn brown.

title: chicken adobo
directions: In a large skillet, arrange chicken in a single layer.
Stir together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and let bubble gently, turning several times until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixer bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar; continue beating at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours before removing from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: broccoli casserole(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: stuff
directions: Place ground beef in an 11-inch stove top pan or electric skillet, pressing to cover bottom of pan.
Spread vegetables over meat.
Pour soup over mixture and place cheese slices on top.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover skillet.
Start with medium-high heat. When mixture starts to steam, turn to low and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together and turn into a greased bread pan.
Set in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash the beans.
Place them in a Dutch oven and cover with water.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Add the ham bone and seasonings to the beans.
Add water to cover the beans.
Cook, partially covered, over medium-low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Cook the rice, according to package directions, 30 minutes before serving.
Add the sliced sausage to the beans 20 minutes before.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican candy
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil and boil until hard ball stage. Stir in grated coconut and pecans.
Stir while cooking for few minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs (gradually).
Stir constantly until thickened.
Spread in buttered round cake pan. Bake at 350° until brown around edges and lightly brown on top. Let cool.
Cut in pieces and store in tin or closed container. (If hard to get out of pan, put over low burner and move back and forth for a few seconds.
Will come out easier, but let get cool after taking from pan.)
Mellows as it ages.

title: chillin' out pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Cool. In a large bowl, stir together yogurt, mustard and herb seasoning. Add pasta, celery and green onions.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, carefully stir in shrimp and tomatoes.
Makes 12 servings.
Calories 140, total fat 1 g.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add both sugars and corn syrup.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Turn heat down and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add maple and vanilla.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Serve with assorted fruit. Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: orange dream ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in 4 quart ice cream freezer. Fill rest of the way with the whole milk.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: chicken salad
directions: Wash and cook chicken well done.
Remove from bone when cool. Use kitchen scissors and cut chicken into small pieces, add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sweet pickles, celery, chopped eggs, vinegar and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve on lettuce leaves or sandwiches.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls in flat or pizza pan to form crust.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix and spread green onions, dill weed, cheese and mayonnaise.
Top with vegetables.
Spread shredded Cheddar cheese and diced tomatoes on top.
Cool.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans by package directions.
Drain.
Combine beans, mushroom soup and almonds in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle stuffing mix evenly on top.
Pour butter or margarine evenly on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab canapes
directions: Blend all ingredients, except muffins.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut muffins in fourths.
Freeze until ready to use. (This works well!)
Broil until edges brown and cheese bubbles. Makes 48.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Add gradually.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: texas chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in 1/2 stick of butter.
Put to side.
Cut chicken in strips and cook in 1/2 stick of butter. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Mix Ro-Tel and soup.
Put 1/2 of mixture into chicken.
Add onion and pepper.

title: spinach stew
directions: Using a medium pot, pour Puritan oil into pot and warm it. Cut the onion and fry, adding the the green pepper, tomatoes and meat or fish.
Add the dill and cinnamon powders and stir.
Let all cook for about 10 minutes and add 1 package of frozen chopped spinach.
Boil until thawed, mixing with other ingredients.
Cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice, potatoes or even bread.

title: pilaf
directions: Brown rice and vermicelli (from soup) in margarine until golden brown.
Add bouillon cube and seasoning from soup to water; bring to boil with browned rice.
Simmer and let steam until dry, about 45 minutes.
Use Uncle Ben's converted rice as it doesn't get sticky and gummy.
Serves 10.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: You will need 2-inch bake cups.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Add tomato soup and water.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Dip chicken in margarine and then in dry ingredients.
Place in pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve with any fresh fruit slices.

title: garden potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, eggs, celery, green onions, radishes, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into 2 round cake pans, 8 or 9-inch.
Do not use pans with removable bottoms.
Bake as directed.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool completely.
Then place each layer back in the (cleaned) cake pans, top side up.
Prick each layer with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight.
Keeps 5 to 6 days in refrigerator.

title: peppernuts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut every 1/2-inch.
Keep dough chilled. Gently pinch with fingers into pyramid shape.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together with beater the peanut butter, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for several hours.
Serve.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Combine sifted flour, salt, soda, baking powder and pecans.
Add to sugar mixture. Blend well.
Roll into balls and wrap in wax paper.
Allow to stand in icebox overnight. Slice very thin.
Put onto greased cookie sheet.
Put into hot oven at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Debone and dice chicken and set aside.
Mix together in large bowl vegetables, potatoes, onions, soup and broth, salt and pepper. Add chicken.
Line casserole dish with 1 pie crust.
Pour in chicken mixture.
Cover mixture with the other pie crust.
Cut 2 to 4 slits for vents to prevent mixture from boiling over.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and turn into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Preparation Time: 10 minutes.
Cooking Time: 25 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Add graham cracker crumbs; pat until smooth.
In layers add chopped nuts, chocolate chips and the coconut.
Pour sweetened condensed milk on top.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: parmesan sprouts
directions: Prepare and cook Brussels sprouts.
Cook and stir onion in margarine until tender.
Pour over Brussels sprouts; sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 125 calories per serving.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, but do not overcook.
Cool, peel and grate. Melt over low heat the butter or margarine and Cheddar cheese. Stir into cheese, then combine with potatoes the sour cream, chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, sugar and salt in mixing bowl and blend well. Stir in nuts. In separate bowl mix eggs, oil, vanilla, pineapple (including juice), bananas and coconut. Add to dry ingredients and mix just until flour mixture is moistened. Grease and flour two 9 X 5 loaf pans. Divide batter into pans and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. These freeze real well.

title: fried rice(from the chinese)
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Saute rice, stirring with a metal spoon 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Stir eggs into rice.
Cook stirring constantly over medium heat, until eggs are cooked, about 3 minutes.
Stir in bacon, soy sauce and pepper; combine well. Garnish with scallions.

title: italian white bean soup
directions: In a large soup pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Saut onion for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot ham puffs
directions: Blend flour with cream cheese and butter until a soft dough is formed.
Chill and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Drop a small bit of ham which has been blended with Worcestershire sauce on circle.
Fold over to form half circle and prick with fork.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake about 10 minutes at 400°.
Yields 100 puffs.

title: christmas coconut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat 10 to 15 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: date and nut chews(cookies)
directions: Beat until light the eggs, salt and almond extract.
Gradually beat in sugar and Karo syrup.
Add dates and nuts; beat well. Fold in sifted flour.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While still hot, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Shape at once into small balls; roll in powdered sugar.
The dates are very hot, so it helps to cover your hands with a thin coat of butter before shaping the balls. Store cookies in an airtight container.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Microwave or grill chicken.
When meat is cool enough to handle, cut into 1/4-inch crosswise strips and set aside.
Combine vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, lemon pepper and garlic powder. Gradually whisk olive oil into dressing.

title: iowa brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; slowly add syrup, then eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Then add flour; beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix all together and place in a casserole.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Coat
inside of large skillet with nonstick spray and heat to medium. Brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken
and pour off drippings.
Add mushrooms and garlic to skillet, stir over low heat until lightly brown.
Add vegetables, thyme, bay leaf and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper the chicken and return to the skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Stir in flour and water until smooth.
Add to pan and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve gravy and vegetables with the chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Cook beef
and
onion
in
skillet until meat is brown; drain. Stir in salt
and
pepper,	then
spread
in pie plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with a wire beater until smooth (about 1 minute). Pour
into pie plate and bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes
out clean
(5 to 8 minutes).
Garnish with lettuce.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
When partially set, put 1/2 in large dish.
Put one pint of sour cream on top of jello. Then add rest of jello.
Let set until firm.

title: spicy-squash pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a blender container, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch round cake or pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 minutes until set.

title: great aunt bess' favorite waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Covered tightly, this lasts two to three days.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix pecans with egg white (do not beat). Mix cinnamon with sugar and mix with nuts. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: To peach pie filling, add pineapple in syrup, strawberries and mandarin oranges.
Drain all juice and sliced bananas.
Add chopped pecans.
Coconut may be added, if you wish.

title: stir-me-nots
directions: Melt margarine; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine, then coconut, then chocolate chips. Pour condensed milk evenly over all ingredients.
Top with chopped walnuts.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 32 pieces.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Cook beans for 1 1/2 hours and add remaining ingredients.

title: cousin allan's chicken
directions: Spray bottom of baking dish with Pam. Place chicken in dish with slices of cheese on each breast. Mix separately Stove Top stuffing and soup plus one can of water. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: crabmeat and shrimp dip
directions: Mix together with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Prepare at least 12 hours in advance.
Cook carrots until tender, but firm.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper; mix with cooled carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate container.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate for 12 or more hours. Drain vegetables to serve.
Save the marinade for your next batch of carrots, onions and peppers.
A great way to get kids and husbands to eat vegetables!

title: killarney bread
directions: Beat all of ingredients except for the topping ingredients with electric mixer.
Put half of batter into 2 greased bread loaf pans.
Sprinkle half of topping mixture on top of batter.
Put remaining batter in and then top with remaining topping mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dark fruitcake
directions: Combine juice concentrate, molasses and raisins in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in candied fruits and peels. Cream butter and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, soda and spices. Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in fruit/peel mixture and nuts.
Mix well until all fruit is coated.
Line one 11 x 4 x 3-inch pan and two 5 1/2 x 3 x 2 1/4-inch pans with heavy paper,
allowing 1/2-inch to extend above all sides.
Pour batter into pans, filling about 3/4 full.
Bake at 275° about 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 hours for large loaf and about 1 1/2 hours for small loaves.
Cool cakes in pans.
Remove. Wrap in foil or clear plastic wrap and store in cool place several weeks. Makes about 3 1/2 pounds fruitcake.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add soda and peanut butter. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in lightly oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These will rise, so shake pan to deflate after 20 minutes of baking and bake about 10 minutes more.

title: cheese pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Add nuts to mixture.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Grease Bundt pan.
Use sugar/cinnamon mix to dust pan.
Place 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture of sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Cool in pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or plain.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs;
add
sugar,
Karo syrup, pecans and butter. Mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Place
mixture	of
all ingredients, except chicken and dry onion soup,
in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass casserole.
Top with the
chicken breasts (raw).
Sprinkle dry onion soup over the chicken;
cover
tightly
with foil.
Do not uncover until baked for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: country chili
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over T.V.P. flakes and ketchup and let stand for 10 minutes. Heat olive oil in large Dutch oven. Over medium heat, saute onion, green pepper and garlic. Sprinkle chili powder, cayenne, cumin and oregano over T.V.P. mixture. Stir and add to mixture in Dutch oven. Cook a few minutes and stir in canned tomatoes, kidney beans, crushed tomatoes and V-8 juice. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes to an hour. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: almost fat-free pizza
directions: Unroll the French loaf bread onto cookie sheet.
Spread the dough with a generous amount of sauce.
Prepare ground turkey by frying and draining any fat from meat.
Sprinkle meat on sauce. Add green peppers, onions and any other vegetables to taste.
Top with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Makes 2 cups of dry mix which is enough for 6 quarts of tea or you may mix one well rounded teaspoonful of dry mix to 1 cup of boiling water and stir well.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine. Saute celery and onion until tender. Add potatoes and broth. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Puree potatoes. Stir in milk and seasonings. Add cheese, croutons and parsley. Good on cold day, lunch or dinner.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Put chocolate in saucepan and melt in 1/4 cup water.
Cool. (May boil water and add chocolate.)
Cream together oleo and cheese.
Gradually add the 2 pounds powdered sugar.
Mix well. Add chocolate mixture to this.
Beat until well blended.
Remove 3 cups (or about 1/2 of this) mixture and set aside, covered.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Heat in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Do not overheat.
Serve with breadsticks, varieties of rye, celery sticks or fresh cauliflower.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Separate into ten biscuits.
Flatten into 5-inch circles. Press each circle into a greased muffin cup.
In skillet, brown beef; drain.
Mix ketchup, sugar, vinegar and chili powder.
Add meat and mix well.
Divide meat mixture among biscuits; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: a cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas. Stir; do not beat.
Will only take a few stirs to mix.
Pour into large Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
May be glazed when cool, if desired.

title: sundown's grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Allow 6 to 8 ounces per person.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine cream drops and butter.
Cook 3 minutes in microwave. Stir well; remove and add peanut butter and pecans.
Put in Pyrex dish.

title: yellow party cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy (about 8 to 10 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer), scraping bowls frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat at medium speed about 2 minutes or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating at low speed after each addition.
Beat 1 minute at end.
Turn batter into two greased and lightly floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly on wire racks.
Fill with Lemon Filling.
Frost with Seven Minute Frosting.
Sprinkle shredded coconut on sides of cake, if desired.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/4 cup butter until wilted.
Blend in flour, stirring well.
Pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes. Add crabmeat to mixture and blend well.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs drizzled with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: jello jiggly lollipops
