directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Let stand to cool for 15 minutes.
Pour into paper cups.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Carefully peel off the paper cups.
Have Mom use a knife to cut each gelatin cup horizontally into 3 round slices. Place a straw into each gelatin circle to create a jiggly lollipop.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Scrub pickles thoroughly and rinse.
Pack closely into quart jars.
Place a head of dill in the top of each jar.
Mix water, vinegar and salt; bring to a boil and pour at once over pickles. Seal jars and store in a cool, dark place for at least 6 weeks before using.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: wild rice and mushrooms
directions: Put all together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Bake cake as directed
on box;
make pudding with 4 1/2 cups of milk.
Break
candy
into
small
pieces.
In
a punch bowl, place 1/2 of the
cake, which has been broken into small pieces, on the bottom of
bowl.
Then sprinkle with 1/4 cup of Kahlua, then 1/2 of
the pudding mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the candy bar, then 1/2 of
the
Cool Whip.
Repeat the steps with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat over low heat.
Serve warm with assorted crackers and breadsticks.
Serves 12.

title: spinach pasta
directions: Cook
spinach
and
drain
very
thoroughly.
Puree
in blender or food processor.	Measure
out
cup	puree
and return to saucepan.
Cook for a minute or two over low heat to dry out as much
as possible.
Combine with flour, eggs, olive oil, salt and nutmeg.
Knead
dough; wrap in plastic and allow to rest at least 20 minutes before rolling and cutting.

title: country inn breakfast bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
In a second larger bowl, combine remaining ingredients in order given. Gradually stir dry mixture into liquid mixture.
Pour batter into 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle topping over loaf.

title: potato stuffing bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
In large saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Remove from heat; add milk and potato flakes, stirring until well blended.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups of the bread cubes (reserve remaining 1/3 for topping), celery, green onions and hot pepper sauce.
Spoon into greased casserole.

title: lime christmas punch
directions: Combine sugar, Kool-Aid and hot water.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
In punch bowl blend sugar syrup, pineapple juice and soda. Spoon in sherbet.
Makes 22 cups.

title: olive-cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add olive juice to make dipping consistency. Dip with favorite chips (plain potato chips, like Ruffles are best).

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except the nuts) and form a ball. Roll in the nuts until evenly coated. Chill until ready to serve. Serve with crackers or garlic toast. Great for holiday parties. To make more attractive, roll in 1/2 cup fresh chopped parsley mixed with the nuts.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt together.

Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or fork until pieces are the size of small peas. Sprinkle water over mixture and blend until all is moistened. Roll into a ball and let stand several minutes.
Roll pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate.
Poke holes in pastry with fork.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: royal peanut butter crackers
directions: Generously spread peanut butter between two crackers or wafers.
Press together so that peanut butter spreads to edge. Melt almond bark according to directions on package.
Dip crackers into melted almond bark.
Place on foil or waxed paper to harden.

title: turkey or chicken wild rice bake
directions: Pour water into casserole dish, stir in rice and seasoning packet mix.
Stir in sliced mushrooms.
Cut artichoke hearts into quarters and stir into rice.
Stir in the pimento and chicken or turkey.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until moisture is gone.
Top with 1 cup shredded Swiss cheese and brown lightly.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Cool Whip (slowly mix well).
Pour into pie crust; then top with cherry pie filling (you may use any fruit filling).
Let set in refrigerator for about 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken diavolo
directions: Sprinkle chicken with parsley, lemon pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Roll up each breast, seasoned side in; secure with toothpicks.
Heat olive oil in large skillet; add chicken and cook until golden brown.
Remove chicken and drain on paper towels. Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Remove toothpicks. Sprinkle artichoke hearts with lemon juice.
Place in casserole around chicken pieces.
Combine wine with spaghetti sauce and pour over chicken and artichokes.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set to blend flavors and juices. If too juicy, squeeze out some of the liquid.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in aluminum foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Open foil; cool.
Cut into large bite-size pieces.
Combine onion, soups, sour cream, chili, salsa and garlic salt; stir until well blended.
Butter a large casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Place a layer of tortilla chips on bottom and a layer of chicken on top.
Spoon salsa-soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with half the olives and cheese.
Repeat layers ending with a layer of cheese.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until bubbly. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash beans, slice onion and peppers.
Heat mixture; pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Shake well before serving.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Bring water and Old Bay seasoning to a boil in a large stockpot. Add potatoes; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes. Add sausage and corn; return to a boil. Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove potatoes, corn and sausage with a slotted spoon. Add shrimp to stockpot; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Remove shrimp with a slotted spoon. Serve with additional Old Bay seasoning, cocktail sauce and butter.

title: boiled rice
directions: Rinse rice under cold water.
Place rice and water in pot. Heat until water begins to boil.
Lower heat and cover pot.
Cook undisturbed for 18 minutes.
Do not peek.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake in large cookie sheet about 20 minutes according to package.
Let cream cheese soften, then mix with vanilla pudding until creamy.
Spread creamy mixture on cooled cake.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas and cut strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate with nuts and strawberries.

title: frozen dill pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, salt and water.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Don't rinse.
Add sugar, vinegar and dill weed.
Let stand until cucumbers are covered with liquid, about 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: mary eckley's jellied cranberry mold
directions: Peel oranges; reserve 1/4 of the peel.
Remove white membrane and seeds, then chop the oranges coarsely.
Wash cranberries; drain.
Remove stems.
Put cranberries through coarse blade of food chopper.
Chop orange peel; it should measure about 3 tablespoons.
Add cranberries.
Add oranges and sugar; mix well and set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice in small saucepan to soften.
Place over low heat, stirring, until gelatin is dissolved.
Add gelatin mixture to cranberry-orange mixture; mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm, 6 to 8 hours.

title: fresh tomato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tomatoes in boiling water until skins loosen slightly, about 1 minute.
Rinse with cold water and remove skins.
Cut tomatoes into quarters; remove seeds and chop (makes about 2 3/4 cups).
Drain very well in a sieve or colander; set aside.

title: mop sauce for barbecue
directions: Cook onion in margarine until clear.
Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Mop onto meat while grilling.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: easy and delicious cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill awhile.
Put into a ball. Roll in pecans, if desired.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix dates, candy, nuts and coconut with 1/4 c. of flour. Set aside.
Add remaining dry ingredients with buttermilk to butter mixture and mix well.
Stir in candy mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
It is great for munching on while on trips and camping. Enjoy.

title: squash cakes
directions: Grate squash with medium grater, making about 2 cups.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and egg.
Mix well, causing mixture to become quite juicy.
Add flour and baking powder.
More or less flour may be needed to obtain proper consistency for dropping by tablespoonfuls into frying pan with hot bacon grease or butter. Cook slowly to golden brown.
Turn cakes and brown other side.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour and salt in a bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup milk, bacon drippings and egg white.
Add to flour mixture all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Add just enough additional milk to make a medium-thin batter.
Peel, wash and dry onions.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Separate onion rings.
Dip each ring into batter. Fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle with salt.

title: grandmother's cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir just until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into balls.	Flatten with fork on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: date-nut pinwheels
directions: In saucepan, cook dates, granulated sugar and water, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Cool.
Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half on waxed paper into rectangle (about 11 x 7-inch).
Spread half of the date-nut filling on each rectangle.
Roll up tightly, beginning at long side.
Pinch edge of dough to seal securely. Wrap and chill at least 4 hours.
May bake immediately or store for up to 6 weeks.
Fifteen minutes before serving, heat oven to 400°. Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: rotini and meat
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet and combine with browned ground meat.
Boil rotini.
Combine with meat.
Add garlic powder and desired amount of catsup.
Any type of pasta may be substituted.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Mix until crumbly the flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt and flour.
Add rhubarb.
Spread on mixture and bake 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine egg, milk and vegetable oil, then add flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add mini chocolate chips.

title: coconut cream cheese cake
directions: Cream first 3 together, then add 3 cups sugar, eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Cream real good.
Then add your flavor and frozen coconut.
Bake in Bundt pan 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken and almond roll(10 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Chill.
Make out into 10 rolls with flattened ends.
Roll in flour.
Dip in egg mixture made of 2 beaten eggs and 2 tablespoons water, strained.
Roll in almonds. Shape into croquettes.
Chill.
Fry in deep fat at 350°, until almonds are toasted a golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper. Serve topped with A La King sauce.

title: artichoke hot dish
directions: Mix and put in baking dish. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: "red lobster" biscuits
directions: Mix together Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix together butter and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits.

title: plant food for ivy or flowers
directions: Add ammonia and soda to water.
Water plants, once a month with this food.
Makes ivy green and have heavy foliage.

title: sausage and cheese brunch tarts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 12 (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups.
Cook and stir sausage until brown; drain.
Mix baking mix and margarine.
Add boiling water.
Stir vigorously until soft dough forms.
Press 1 level tablespoon dough on bottom and up sides of each cup.
Divide sausage evenly among cups.
Beat half and half and egg.
Stir in onions and salt.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon into each cup.
Sprinkle cheese over tops.
Bake until edges are golden brown about 25 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: charcoal steak sauce
directions: Mix all together, simmer 30 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 25 grilled steaks.

title: okra soup
directions: In a large stock pot, combine the soup bones, onion and 2 quarts of water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to moderate heat, cover and simmer for two hours.
Remove the soup bones, dice the meat, discard the bones and return meat to the pot.
In a small skillet or in the microwave, extract and discard excess fat from bacon bits.
Stir in the okra, tomatoes, bacon, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Discard the bay leaf.
Serves 8.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° until done.
Stir in remaining ingredients and continue cooking until bubbling.
Good to serve over noodles.

title: congealed salad
directions: Cream together the cheese, sugar and margarine.
Drain fruit and pineapple. Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook about 35 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: country raisin gingersnaps
directions: Beat butter, egg and sugar.
Blend in molasses, flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins.
Chill for a few hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Shape into walnut size balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Put on lightly greased baking pan and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar -- beat until lemon colored.

title: devil's delight
directions: Crumble cookies in bottom of cake pan.
Layer with pudding and Cool Whips.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on bottom.
Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, melted margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve from pan.

title: stickies
directions: Mix together as for biscuit dough.

title: party sandwiches(egg filling)
directions: Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs in a bowl.
Mix in flour, a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 20 minutes and then turn oven to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables(for clay pot)
directions: Soak clay pot.
Layer onions on bottom.
Dot with margarine, salt and pepper.
Add remaining vegetables in order.
Dot each layer generously with butter, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Put into cold oven. Turn temperature to 425°.
Bake 40 minutes.
Open pot and stir vegetables lightly.
Cover and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain liquid from vegetables.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish, starting with beans, then add onion over vegetables.
Combine celery soup and sour cream.
Pour over vegetables and onion.
Melt margarine; add to cracker crumbs.
Spread over casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gen's salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cheese and mix.
Add pineapple and mix. Fold in whipped topping.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix
peaches
and
lemon
juice together in small bowl. Blend melted
butter, sugar, flour, cinnamon and eggs, mixing together. Pour over peaches.	Toss gently. Spoon peaches into unbaked pie shell.
Put
strips
of
pie crust on top of pie. Bake 50 to 60 minutes; after 15 to 20 minutes baking, put foil around outer rim of crust to keep crust from getting brown.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup tomato sauce and other ingredients in a bowl. Shape into 2-inch balls and place in baking dish.
Add 1 cup water to remaining tomato sauce and pour over meatballs.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg white, dry milk and water until stiff.
Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until very stiff.
Beat in egg yolk just until mixed.
Fold in pie filling.
Freeze 4 hours or more.
Makes 1 quart of sherbet.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: ramen salad
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Saute noodles, seed and almonds until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Place torn lettuce, onions and meat choice in large salad bowl.
Add noodle mixture.
Toss with dressing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add beef; mix well. Pat mixture into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Spoon off excess fat. Combine ketchup, brown sugar and mustard. Spread over meat. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry and orange mold
directions: Grind raw cranberries and whole small oranges together and add sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
In the meantime, make jello and cool until almost stiff.
Add cranberry mixture and mix together. Pour into ring mold and chill until firm.
Turn onto platter. Fill center with lettuce or parsley.

title: seafood pasta supreme(a great idea by linda)
directions: Combine noodles and cream cheese in medium bowl.
Spread noodle mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook seafood in butter over medium heat until prawns are pink and tender, about 5 minutes. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic. Spread seafood over noodle mixture.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir hamburger in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until light brown.
Remove from heat; drain.
Stir in onion, sour cream, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Cover and reserve.

title: cindy's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into ball.

title: baptist punch(always a favorite)
directions: Mix together and put into freezer to slush.
It may be colored with food coloring if you desire.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients
and pour over crushed ice.
Add ginger ale to taste.

title: dill and cheese bread
directions: Cut loaf of bread in crisscross pattern almost to bottom of loaf but not quite through.
Melt margarine and add dill.
With a pastry brush, brush margarine mixture on the inside of each cut in the bread.
Slice cheese into thin squares and tuck into each cut in the bread.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Place in preheated oven for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Pieces can easily be torn off.

title: wrapped cauliflower
directions: Core cauliflower but do not break apart.
Parboil whole hea d for 5 minutes.
Leave head intact.
Carefully remove from water and drain.
Place head in round baking dish.
Fill inside with cheeses and bacon.
Pour heavy cream and 1 tablespoon melted butter over cauliflower.
Arrange 1 sheet filo over cauliflower, tacking it around the head.
Brush sheet of dough with butter. Place other sheets around head over each other brushing each with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt oleo in a double boiler, then add caramels.
Melt and stir.
Add nuts.
Drop on greased foil with teaspoon.
Place a toothpick in each.
Cool!
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip caramelized nuts in chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: herb onion salad dressing
directions: In blender, combine vinegar, sugar and onion and process until smooth. Add seasonings. Cover and blend well. Gradually add oil in a steady stream. Blend until thickened.

title: peanut  butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into crust and freeze.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix everything together and roll into balls.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool for 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter with a fork and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until golden brown, then cool. Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of Cool Whip and spread on cool crust.
Then mix instant puddings together using 3/4 of milk called for on box and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then spread other half of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with pecans.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cook bacon and use grease to cook the pork chops, peppers and onion.
Cook rice separately.
Mix all ingredients.
Add soy sauce. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until pork chops are done.

title: emergency muffins
directions: Stir egg in glass measuring cup. Fill cup up to 1/2 cup with cooking oil. Fill cup up to 1 cup with sweet milk. Combine liquid and flour. Grease muffin tin. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange jupiter
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender until smooth.
With blender running at lowest speed, add ice cubes, one at a time; blend smooth.
Serve at once.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: red cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Combine cocoa, vanilla, vinegar, salt and food coloring. Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk, cake flour and soda.
Mix well. Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool, then split layer with thread to make 4 layers.

title: watermelon preserves
directions: Cook rind in water to cover until tender. Drain. Make syrup of water and sugar. Add rind and lemon juice. Cook until clear. If possible add a couple of slices of lemon, also if you like ginger root, add a little.

title: brownie bites
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in two or 3-quart pan over lowest heat until melted.
Remove pan and stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour. Spoon into paper lined tiny muffin tins, filling almost to top. Place nut on top of batter.
Bake at 325° until tops look dry and feel firm when touched, about 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Transfer to rack to cool.
Serve warm or cool.
To store, let cool, then package airtight and hold room temperature up to 4 days.
Makes 40.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine in a bowl.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all other ingredients; do not drain.
Salt and pepper may be added to taste.
Heat until ingredient flavors are blended.

title: italian knots
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, then add flour (one cup at a time) and remaining dry ingredients. melt butter and add to batter.
Mix well.
(You'll get to know how the texture should feel.)
Roll into balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
The dough should not stick to your hands when rolling cookies into shape.
Add more flour if necessary.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all but Cool Whip and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cream the butter and flour.
Add chicken broth and water; bring to a boil, then add salt, pepper, mushrooms and broccoli. Cook until broccoli is done.
Stir frequently.

title: mushroom soup bread with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine honey, mushroom soup, water, salt and dry onion flakes.
Warm mixture slightly. In a large bowl, combine 3 1/2 cups of flour with yeast and mix. Gradually add soup mixture to flour and stir.
Add cheese and mix thoroughly for several minutes.
Gradually add almost all of the remaining flour (reserve about 1/2 cup).
Turn dough out on floured surface and knead; add remaining flour.
Knead dough for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place dough in large bowl sprayed with butter flavor nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and let rise until doubled (about 2 hours).

title: betty's white fruit cake
directions: Cream butters and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time alternately with flour.
Dredge fruit in about 1 cup of the flour and add to creamed mixture.
Cook in 3 loaf pans (9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch), greased and lined with brown paper and greased inside before mix is added to pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes (sometimes takes 2 hours).
Cook in tin pans set in pan of water while baking to add moisture.

title: old-fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and Crisco; add egg yolks and flavorings.
Next add buttermilk.
Blend in 1 cup of flour at a time.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: angel custard
directions: Mix thoroughly graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and the 1/2 cup sugar and pat evenly into a good-sized dish.
Soak gelatin in milk for 1/2 hour, then add 1 cup sugar and beaten egg yolks. Cook until it boils and cool thoroughly.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into cooked custard that has been cooled. Whip the cream and fold into custard and egg whites.
Pour into crust and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Add generous amount of seasoned salt on each piece of chicken.
Put in a shallow baking dish or crock-pot. Mix the cream soups and the milk together.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered with foil.
If put in crock-pot, let it cook for 2 hours also.
Soups will make a good, creamy gravy.

title: oklahoma pork chops
directions: Salt, pepper and brown chops on both sides.
Turn heat down to 300°.
Place a slice of lemon on each chop and pour sauce made of ketchup, brown sugar and wine over all.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently so brown sugar does not burn.
You can also bake in oven at 350°, covered, for the same amount of time.
Time is not critical as long as heat is low.
Delicious and even the lemon slices taste good.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: canyon bread
directions: Cut center out of rye bread. Cream together all remaining ingredients.
Put in hollowed out rye bread, cover with foil. Bake at 325° about 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage. Drain off fat drippings, then add in chopped onion and green bell peppers. Cook until onions and green peppers are tender. Put all cooked ingredients in crock-pot and add cream cheese. Cook on low until cream cheese has melted. Then serve with tortilla chips.

title: icebox cookies(a dutch recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together; blend well.
Add dry mixture and nuts to the sugar mixture.
(Dough will be thick; you may have to use your hands to blend.)
Roll into logs; wrap in wax paper.
Makes approximately 5 logs (10 to 12 inches long and 2 inches in diameter).
Refrigerate 1 day before using.

title: milk gravy
directions: To make milk gravy, pour off most of the fat.
Add 2 tablespoons of flour and let brown slightly in the remaining grease.
Add milk (as much gravy as you want); salt and pepper to taste and boil briefly.
Serve with potatoes or any bread or biscuits.

title: no fuse apricot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven with lid.
Cook in 250° oven for at least 5 hours.
DO NOT PEEK!
The longer it cooks, the better it gets.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and a dash or two of Worcestershire sauce in a skillet until beef is brown.
Drain beef on paper towels.
Meanwhile, pour tomatoes, pintos and 1 package of seasoning into a large pot and start to cook.
Put beef back into skillet and mix with the other package of seasoning and water. Simmer 5 minutes and then add to pot.
Mix together well.
Cook 30 minutes to 2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put layer of potatoes in large pan; top with cheese and ham, then pats of oleo, salt and flour.
Repeat this layer.
Pour warm milk over top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: wesson oil pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add milk to Wesson oil, don't stir.
Pour into flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Roll between wax paper.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Also use as with any unbaked pie shell.

title: cabbage wedge meal-in-one
directions: Remove tough outside leaves from cabbage; discard.
Cut head in 6 to 8 wedges.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole.
Arrange onion, beef and rice between wedges.
Combine tomatoes and seasonings; pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal into mixing bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix well.
Blend in eggs and sweetener.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.

title: feather light pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend until smooth and bake on a hot griddle.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scramble egg french fries
directions: Fry potatoes, then drain off oil.
Mix egg and milk.
Pour egg mix over potatoes and scramble.
Serve hot!

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and mix all ingredients together, putting noodles last.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes large hot dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Add 1/2 of dry ingredients and 1/2 of buttermilk.
Then add remaining dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Flour and grease 2 big loaf pans and 1 small loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, instant vanilla pudding (dry) and drained crushed pineapple.
Mold into a cheese ball.
Cover with pecans.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except bread.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Crumble bread on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: calamai-coconut pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and heat over low heat; stirring constantly is necessary until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Pour into shallow pan and cool.
Cut into squares or wedges and serve.
This will serve about 10 people.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a sauce pan, mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until very thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Let pie cool and top with Cool Whip or whipped egg whites.

title: faster and flameless candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan or electric skillet. Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat (or turn off electric skillet).
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cornflakes and stir until all are coated with syrup mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: turkey cheese surprise
directions: Mix ground turkey, stuffing, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, apples and poultry seasoning.
Add garlic salt, pepper and onions. Add eggs and Ricotta cheese and blend all together.
Cut Mozzarella cheese into cubes.
Form meat mixture around these cheese cubes.

title: cold taco salad
directions: Heat beans just to lightly warm.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break chips up to cover the bottom of pan.
Spread beans over chips. Cover beans with sour cream.
Cover sour cream with lettuce, then layer on cheese, tomatoes and onions.
Chill.
Don't chill too long or your chips may get soft.

title: let the oven do the work
directions: Melt butter.
Toss roast and potatoes in butter.
Take roast out and broil until brown (both sides).
Boil carrots 10 minutes in beef broth.
Spray pan or baking dish with Pam spray.
Pour meat, potatoes, carrots and broth in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Tender and delicious.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add celery and onion to browned meat. Cover with water and cook slowly, uncovered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Add soy sauce, brown sugar and mushrooms.
Add bean sprouts and liquid.
Thicken gravy to desired consistency.
Serve over chow mein noodles or cooked rice or both.
Serves 8.

title: oven barbecue beef brisket
directions: Place beef brisket in container; sprinkle with liquid smoke. Cover and marinate overnight.
Drain.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and salts.
Bake covered at 250° for 4 to 6 hours (according to size; 4 pounds for 3 hours, 5 pounds for 4 hours and 6 pounds for 5 hours) until tender.
Drain and top with barbecue sauce and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift first six ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased bread pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute celery and onions in oleo.
Add cooked rice.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add to rice mixture.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz. Bake about 20 minutes in a 300° to 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bread baked in a jar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.

Add to pumpkin mixture. Stir in nuts. Pour mixture into greased wide-mouth pint jars filling 1/2 full. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. When done, remove one jar at a time, clean sealing edge with paper towel and screw cap on.
Heat will vacuum seal jar and the bread will last up to one year. Makes 8 pint jars.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into straws and bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: fanny's fudge
directions: Butter large pie pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Cook until small ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat.

title: oven-barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain fat.
Place slices of lemon and onion on ribs.
Put remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Put in a 350° oven and bake about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: easy she crab soup
directions: Mix and heat ingredients.
Add twist of lemon on top of each bowl.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Let set at room temperature for 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Shape into balls (size of walnut). Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Good for party!

title: potato cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	In a medium bowl, combine meat, crumbs, 1
egg,
green
pepper,
onion and bouillon; mix well. Use as a shell in a 9-inch pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Pour off fat. In	a
medium
saucepan,
heat water, butter and salt to boiling. Remove
from heat; add sour cream and potato flakes. Stir in 1 egg and 1/2 of cheese;
spoon into shell.
Bake for 10 minutes. Top with remaining cheese; bake 5 minutes longer. Let stand
for 5
minutes.
Top
with
lettuce and tomato, if desired.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix.
Bake covered at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tortillas(low-fat)
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and chop.
Roll chicken and cheese in tortillas.
Combine soup and yogurt.
Mix well.
Pour sauce over top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Optional:
Add sliced jalapenos over top after removing from oven and ready to serve.

title: "souper" easy supper
directions: Lightly brown ground beef or turkey.
Drain off any grease that accumulates.
Add a tablespoon or so of flour and a can of Campbell's French onion soup.
Heat for a while until it thickens and meat is thoroughly cooked.
We serve it several ways, on soft hamburger buns with chips and fruit salad or on toast with vegetables and salad.
Easy and good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all except cut-up chicken until smooth.
Stir in chicken. Put in Pyrex dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with margarine.
Top chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet or wok. Add chicken and onion; stir and cook over high heat until chicken is lightly browned. Combine cornstarch with soy sauce and broth. Add to skillet along with the vegetables. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Makes 3 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops (no oil needed). Remove from pan and lightly saute onions and peppers in this pan.
Mix all but pork chops together and put in casserole dish. Top with pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garbage bread
directions: Thaw bread and roll out.
Spread Grey Poupon on bread. Sprinkle on salt and oregano.
Make layers, starting with ham, then Provolone cheese, salami, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: heath brickle crunch cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt. Cream sugar and oleo. Add eggs and vanilla. Slowly blend in dry ingredients. Blend in chips and nuts. Drop on cookie sheet. If oleo is used instead of butter, 1/2 cup more flour is needed. Oleo has quite a lot of water in it. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Brush bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Mix Parmesan cheese, Bisquick, seasoning, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken. Arrange skin sides down.

title: cherry winks
directions: Measure corn flakes; crush into coarse crumbs.
Set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Measure margarine and sugar into large bowl; beat until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Mix until combined; stir in nuts, dates and the finely-cut cherries.
Shape level tablespoons of dough into balls. Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheets. Top each cookie with a cherry quarter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheet and cool on wire rack. Yield:
about 5 dozen, 2 inches in diameter.

title: pimento cheese sandwich filling
directions: Stir together in medium saucepan granulated sugar and flour. Add beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Stir mixture over medium heat until thickened.
Add butter.
Cool in same pan in refrigerator a couple hours.
Mix together in food grinder Colby cheese, pimentos and hard-boiled eggs.
Combine sauce and cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Season with salt and pepper. Cool several hours before making sandwiches.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain 1 can asparagus.
Add soup and crushed potato chips to all asparagus with 1 can of liquid.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Bake at 275° for 35 minutes.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts.
Add salsa or picante sauce and diet Coke.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until sauce has thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: english trifle
directions: Layer broken pieces of stale cake in a casserole dish.
Cover with jam, then pour boiled custard over both.
Steam or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix together all ingredient in desired amounts.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Stir and add more mayonnaise or seasonings as necessary.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together Milnot, water, sugar, salt and Crisco. Beat 3 eggs into mix.
Then mix together water, sugar and yeast.
Add to mixture. Add 3 cups flour. Beat well with mixer. Let rise a little. Then add enough flour to knead a little (about 7 cups). Let rise again. Put in pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350°.

title: creamy turkey or chicken and pasta primavera
directions: In
a 4-quart saucepan, prepare the mostaccioli or ziti according to package directions.
Add broccoli, carrot, onions and red
pepper in the last 5 minutes of cooking time.	Drain. In same saucepan,	combine
soup,	water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring
occasionally.
Add
mostaccioli
or
ziti mixture and turkey or chicken.	Heat thoroughly in a low oven.

title: friday night special(mexican casserole)
directions: Brown ground beef; season to taste with salt and pepper; drain.
Tear 3 to 4
tortillas and cover the bottom of a 9x13 baking dish.
Spoon half of the meat over tortillas.
Mix soup and tomatoes together in a bowl; spoon half of mixture over meat. Drain beans and spoon half over soup mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over beans.
Layer the remaining ingredients in same order. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes; edges should be brown and the top bubbly.

title: b&b* crunchy peanut butter pie
directions: Allow ice cream to melt to consistency of Cool Whip, then blend all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Place in freezer approximately 4 hours.
Makes 2 pies.
Enjoy!!!!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and salt until tender.
While broccoli boils, crush Ritz crackers with rolling pin.
Then melt butter.
Add melted butter to crackers in mixing bowl and mix well.
When broccoli is done put in casserole dish.
Cut up Velveeta and stir into broccoli.
Add 3/4 of cracker mix, stir well.
Sprinkle remaining cracker mix on top and pack.
Cook 30 minutes at 300° or 350°.

title: beef with snow peas and baby corn
directions: Brown beef in wok or large skillet.
Drain.
Add garlic; cook until tender.
Set aside.
Wipe wok with paper towel.
Heat vegetable oil in wok over medium-high.
Add snow peas and red bell pepper; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in ground beef mixture, baby corn, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove and cool.
Add salt, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Will set up fast if not careful.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients and smear on top of chicken.
Place chicken in a shallow pan.
Baste chicken every 20 to 30 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
The slower and longer you cook, the more it will glaze.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and mix.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and onion; cook until brown.
Drain fat off, then add macaroni and spaghetti sauce.
Stir it up well.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 1 hour before serving.
Pie filling mix and pineapple should be in same size container (not same weight).

title: easy chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat 10 to 12 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Spread one-half of crumb mixture in bottom of a large dish.
Cream with mixer the cream cheese and sugar.
Mix cold milk with Dream Whip.
Beat until stiff and then add to cream cheese.
Spread one-half of this mixture on cracker crumbs.
Add pie filling.
Spread last half of cream cheese.
Add rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Chill at least 24 hours.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix in order.
Fold in cranberries last.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.

title: beer pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix soup mix, beer, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Put pork chops in casserole and pour the rest of the ingredients over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sweet rice
directions: Combine milk, sugar and vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Turn off heat and add rice. Cover until all liquid is absorbed into the rice.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Beat eggs with water until light.
Add sugar and mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: maraschino cherry bars
directions: Blend until crumbly and press in ungreased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat and simmer, covered 15 minutes.
Stir together cornstarch and milk.
Add to chowder along with corn. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage soup(serves many)
directions: Saute sausage (remove casing first) with garlic and onions. Add beef broth, water, red wine, tomatoes, carrots, basil and oregano.
Cook 1 hour.
One hour before serving, add sliced zucchini, tortellini, parsley and green pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves many.

title: veggie pizza
directions: One day ahead, mix together cream cheese, mayo, Ranch packet, onion salt and garlic salt, then refrigerate for several hours.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper together and shape into patties.
Brown lightly in frying pan.
Place patties in a baking dish.
Combine catsup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire and onion for sauce.
Pour over meat and bake very slowly for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate cheese cups
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend on high until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl; set aside.
Combine egg whites and salt in a medium bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Coat paper muffin pan liners with cooking spray.
Sprinkle evenly with graham cracker crumbs.
Spoon batter into liners, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in oven 30 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 16.

title: hopscotch's
directions: Melt the morsels over hot water, stir in peanut butter. Mix in lrg. bowl the
marshmallows and noodles;
add the butterscotch mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by heaping tsp. onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill until set.

title: meat loaf(from 1975 edition)
directions: Add meat, salt, pepper, eggs (slightly beaten) and onion.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into a loaf; place in a pan and lay bacon across the top.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 1 1/2 hours, basting with 1/2 cup hot water.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces and put in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer the following vegetables on the lettuce: peppers, celery, green onions and frozen peas.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and the Ranch dressing and mix well. Spread over the frozen peas and top with the shredded cheese and then the crumbled bacon.
Cover tightly and leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Place small cucumbers in quart jars.
Add garlic, onion, hot red pepper and dill seed.
Set aside while you bring to boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Let set 3 weeks before using.
Makes approximately 7 quarts.

title: cheesy mushroom meat loaf
directions: Put hamburger in bowl.
Add beefy mushroom soup, eggs, crackers, onion, half of broth, both kinds of cheese and salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberries and cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar with mixer until smooth.
Set aside.
Whip whipping cream until real stiff (almost to butter).
Fold together with cream cheese and sugar mixture and pour in prepared pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with strawberries with serving.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth but still icy.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 cups.

title: cranberry bundt cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Fold in the cranberries and pecans. Pour into a greased and floured 8-inch fluted pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Peel and shred zucchini/
Mix with canning salt and let sit overnight.
Next morning, put in colander and let drain.
Add zucchini with all other ingredients and bring to full boil.
Fill jars and process for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with juice from pineapple.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor or beat with mixer. Serve with all types of fresh vegetables.

title: tuna casserole 1
directions: Save 1 cup of shoestring potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Place 1 cup of potatoes on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: oriental noodles(international)
directions: Saute garlic in cooking oil until golden brown, then add onion, pork, carrot and cabbage.
Season with soy sauce and fry for 2 minutes.
Add broth and simmer.
Add celery.
When vegetables are cooked, mix in soaked and drained rice noodles and season. Optional:
green onions to garnish.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts.
Place in 2-quart ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute
beef, onion, celery and garlic in oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add	water
and
bouillon; bring to a boil.	Add cabbage, carrots,
chickpeas
and kidney beans.
Reduce heat. Cover	and simmer
for
minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, parsley	and seasonings;
simmer
for 15 minutes longer.
Add macaroni.	Cook until pasta is tender.

title: breasties
directions: Coat boned chicken breasts with melted butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip in a mixture of equal parts of Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Make pudding as directed on box.
Crumble half the cake into punch bowl then pour half the pudding, layer on top, then layer half the pineapple and pie filling.
Repeat method.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill well and serve.

title: chinese beef and vegetables
directions: Cut steak diagonally
across
the
grain into very thin slices, then cut into strips 2-inches long.
Heat salad oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add meat and brown well on all sides.
Add green
peppers,
celery,
mushrooms,
onion,
bean sprouts,
water chestnuts,
salt,
ginger
and
black
pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, just until tender, about 3 minutes. Blend together cornstarch,
beef bouillon and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture and
cook,
stirring constantly, until smooth and mixture comes to a
boil.
Serve
immediately
with hot cooked rice and additional soy
sauce
or egg noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grate or grind the cabbage, apple and onion together.
Mix salad dressing, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pepper together. Pour over slaw.

title: christmas cut-out cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt on wax paper.
Beat together butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy; beat in flour mixture on low speed until combined.
Leave dough in bowl, but divide in half.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
(It may be necessary to let dough soften slightly at room temperature before rolling out cookies.)

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Melt butter and add to peanut butter.
When blended well, add powdered sugar, then add Rice Krispies.
Mix well and form 1-inch balls.

In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Place dipped chocolate balls on wax paper to cool or you can place dipped balls on a lightly buttered cookie sheet and place in the refrigerator to harden.
Look out thighs!

title: banana split dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch cake pan with graham crackers.
Whip butter, eggs and powdered sugar until smooth and spread on top of crumbs.
Spread completely to sides of pan, sealing off crumbs. Slice bananas over mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Layer Cool Whip over pineapple and sprinkle with nuts. Keep cold.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Pour mixture over lettuce.
Add Fritos.
Serve immediately. Do not store marinated mixture and lettuce together.

title: betty's cheese cake
directions: Crush zwieback and put into 8-inch spring pan, lightly buttered.
Set out cream cheese to soften.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Blend in 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg white mixture and vanilla.
Blend well until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch spring pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Mix sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and spread on top.
Bake 5 minutes at 475°.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn upside down and serve with fruit.

title: easy cheddar fondue
directions: In a 2-quart pan (or fondue pot), combine soup, sherry, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine cheeses and flour and add. Heat over low; stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Dip crusty French bread, ham and apples.

title: garlic herb chicken supreme
directions: Spray cake size pan with Pam. Put chicken in pan, sprinkle with garlic and herb seasonings. Bake 350° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, saute bacon, onion, mushrooms.
When almost done add garlic.
Place spoonfuls of bacon mixture on each piece of chicken.
Add spoonfuls of sour cream, 1/2 piece Swiss cheese and top with both soups.
Sprinkle with basil, thyme, poultry seasoning and rosemary.
Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes more.

title: delicious potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook potatoes.
They should be just tender, not mushy.	Add 1 cup milk and heat.
In medium bowl, mix sour cream, flour, chives and remaining 1 cup milk. Gradually stir sour cream mixture into soup base.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Makes 6 cups.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef, refried beans and taco seasoning.
Stuff uncooked manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Place in greased (9 x 13-inch) baking dish.
Pour water and picante/salsa over top of shells.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Cheddar; return, uncovered, to oven until melted.
Top with sour cream, black olives and green onions.

title: noodleburger scallop
directions: Brown beef and cook celery with garlic until tender.
Pour off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, blend soups, milk and sour cream.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer noodles, meat and soup mixtures.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: congo bars
directions: Combine
all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Soak garlic in oil at least 20 minutes (or longer if you really like strong garlic taste).
Mix rest of ingredients in jar.
I have eliminated the raw egg and noticed no change in taste.
Add oil to mixture, straining garlic.
Can add some of garlic to dressing. Mix well.

title: eye opener(drink)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter.
Add crawfish; cook for about 10 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Tony's seasoning to taste.
Add water; cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.
You can also use shrimp if you don't have crawfish.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt into scalded milk.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla.
After completely cooled, pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.
Chill before serving.

title: sweet - n - sour ribs
directions: Season ribs.
Add this mixture to the ribs and refrigerate 24 hours.
Pour excess liquid out of pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover and baste every 5 minutes for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients; cut up fruit and dip!

title: barley casserole
directions: In a large casserole with lid, combine onion, butter and garlic.
Cover and microwave on High 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and microwave 5 minutes on High, then 20 minutes on Medium.
Don't stir while cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
This is delicious and great with chicken.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: In a large bowl, pour water over rice, let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add to rice with remaining ingredients except almonds.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound down boneless chicken breasts.
Place slice of Provolone cheese on top; add thin slice of favorite ham.
Roll up and pierce with toothpick to hold together.
Arrange pieces in flat baking dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well before serving. Makes 1 gallon.

title: cheese and spinach soup
directions: Cook onion and celery
in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add
milk and cook until thickened and mixture bubbles.
Add
spinach and cheese.	Cover and stir until cheese melts.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Spray three 9-inch round cake pans with nonstick coating. Pour batter equally into 3 pans and bake 20 minutes (test for doneness).
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes and remove from pans to cool completely.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain cooked spinach well and mix with all other ingredients. Shape into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen before baking to use later.
Makes 60 to 70 balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and cut up chicken.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir together.
Sprinkle some of the French fried onions on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Pour into greased oblong dish.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and mold to shape desired.
Mix tomato soup, sugar, vinegar and mustard together and pour over meat loaf. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Cut up dates, add boiling water and soda. Set to one side to cool while you beat egg.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Stir.
Add date mixture and 2 3/4 cups flour alternately.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.
Use 5 1/2 x 3-inch
loaf pans to bake.

title: snappy bean dip
directions: Place drained beans and remaining ingredients, except 1 tablespoon of the green onions, in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Or, mash beans to puree and mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in small bowl and garnish with 1 tablespoon chopped green onions.
Serve as a dip with crisp, raw vegetables or chips.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dip or 24 servings.

title: jalapeno buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine buttermilk and next 6 ingredients; whisk well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: low calorie banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
In dish, layer graham crackers, then bananas, then pudding.
Repeat another layer until all is used.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
This makes a good low-calorie dessert.

title: aunt marie's bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well (whisk works well).
Break bread slices into melted margarine.
Pour milk and egg mixture over bread.
Sprinkle with raisins, if desired.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375° until set in middle.

title: marinated carrots with sauce
directions: Drop sliced carrots in salted boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender, but crisp.
Drain.
In a baking dish, layer carrots, onions and peppers in a baking dish, ending with carrots. Mix tomato soup, sugar, oil and vinegar; cook and bring to a boil. Pour over layered carrots.
Cover.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; add orange juice to equal 3/4 cup liquid.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add orange juice mixture, egg, vanilla and almond extract; stir only until moist. Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon batter into a loaf pan lined with greased paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool, cut into thin slices.
Can be made ahead and wrapped in foil, then put in freezer.

title: tofu pie
directions: Drain tofu; mash and mix in a small bowl and set aside.
In a larger bowl, mix together jello, lemon juice and lemon extract. Add tofu and blend well.
Chill until slightly gelled and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and chill well.
Using the other 8 ounces of Cool Whip, top the tofu pies.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Boil until real thick.
Cool before pouring over fruit.
Use any combination of fresh fruit, cut up.
Mix well.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Mix well and chill 1 hour before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and enough water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Blend cranberry sauce in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add to jello.
Pour into mold or 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pineapple should be added last after jello is partially set, so it stays mixed.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Crush pretzels and add melted margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Spread into a 9 x 13 pan and bake for 10 minutes at 375°. Let cool.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift 3 cups of the flour with the salt and spices; set aside. Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Beat together until light. Next, add the molasses and vinegar, then the dry ingredients.
Add soda dissolved in boiling water last.
If necessary, add more flour to make a soft dough.
Drop by soup spoon or tablespoon onto a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix butter and crumbs.
Save half for top.
Put remainder on bottom of 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add slightly softened ice cream and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Put over cracker crust.
Add rest of crumbs for topping.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt enough butter to soften celery and onion.
Cook to soften, not brown.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Put all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: garden pie
directions: Grease two 9-inch pie plates.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: underwood holiday dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese and deviled ham.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper; beat until smooth.
Chop bell peppers fine and stir in mixture.
Makes 3 cups.

title: tortellini salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook tortellini according to package; drain and cool.
Mix the oil, vinegar, basil, tarragon, sugar, salt and pepper well.
Mix tortellini with cheese, olives, tomatoes, onions and peppers. Pour dressing over all.
Chill.

title: chicken log
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Blend in next 2 ingredients and 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Refrigerate remaining parsley.
Shape mixture into a 9-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Toss together remaining parsley and almonds; use to coat log.
Makes 3 cups of spread.

title: iowa carrot cookies
directions: Cream 3/4 cup margarine and sugar. Add eggs, then cooked carrots, vanilla and lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Bake for 12 minutes at

title: hot wings
directions: Bake wings on broiler pan at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn after 1/2 hour.
Melt butter in microwave; add red hot and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Put baked wings in container, pour sauce over and shake.

title: mexican stuffed peppers
directions: Remove stems and white membrane from peppers. Rinse and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in a little water until tender. Add turkey, rice, raisins, brown sugar, vinegar, chili powder, cumin, cinnamon, coriander, salt and pepper.
Stir in Mozzarella.
Place peppers in casserole sprayed with Pam.
Stuff with filling.
Any leftover filling can be place around peppers.
Cover with Saran Wrap. Microwave on Medium until peppers are tender.
Remove wrap. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and cilantro. Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix cheese in soup (may melt, if desired).
Add hominy and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well.
Top with crushed Fritos.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes until heated through and bubbly.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Put in pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Beat egg and blend in soups; add bread crumbs.
Shred chicken and place in buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture in dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana-oatmeal muffins
directions: Blend margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add egg whites.
Beat in mashed bananas.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Lightly oil muffin tins.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: my favorite lasagne recipe
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown and onion and pepper are tender.
Drain well.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes; stir occasionally.
Mix next 5 ingredients, stirring well; set aside.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Gradually add flour to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Chill for ease in handling.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on baking sheet.
With bottom of glass, flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Press pecan half into center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven
until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove to wire racks to cool.

title: aunt pat's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl until blended well.
Mixture will be smooth with a cake-like consistency.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Top with chocolate chips, nuts, coconut, sugar, cherries, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Top with sugar and let cool.

title: creamy caesar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss with 8 cups torn romaine lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole; stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Medium-low 60 to 70 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Peel and quarter potatoes. Peel carrots and cut in 2-inch pieces.
Peel onions and leave whole.
Add, with celery, to meat and stir, to coat with meat juices.
Cover; microwave at High 25 to 30 minutes.
Add peas. Cover; microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: linda's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve next day with sliced fresh vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Take chicken from bones.
Chop up. Mix the stuffing mix, corn bread crumbs and margarine.
Combine in a bowl and mix with hands.
Put 1 layer of crumbs in a baking dish. Top with chopped chicken.
Mix chicken soup and 1 can of broth. Pour over chicken.
Add a few more crumbs.
Mix celery soup with 1 can of broth; pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are golden brown.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: In frypan, place small amount of oil and place onion and pepper in.
Fry slightly to soften.
Add parsley, pepper, tomato paste and sugar.
Mix and then add corned beef; break up in pieces.
If looks a little dry, then add water to mixture gradually.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours until corned beef is very fine.
If too watery, remove lid and allow to cook down.
Serve on buns.

title: herb-marinated chicken(makes 6 servings)
directions: Place cleaned chicken in a heavy plastic bag.
For marinade, in a bowl combine wine, oil, vinegar, basil, oregano, onion salt and garlic.
Pour over chicken in bag.
Close bag and coat chicken well.
Marinate for 5 to 24 hours in refrigerator, turning bag occasionally.

title: cheesy potatoes casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Chill.
Peel and grate potatoes; combine cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons of butter in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter and cheese melt.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine ground beef, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, egg, onion and bread crumbs in bowl.
Mix lightly but well. Form mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown meatballs on all sides in hot oil in 10-inch skillet.
Remove meatballs as they brown. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Pour off fat, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Blend flour into reserved fat in skillet. Stir in tomatoes, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar and basil. Stir well. Add potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Pour over meatballs in casserole.
Cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Mix angel food cake into mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill. May add whipped topping on top if desired.

title: connie's potato casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and pour into 3 quart casserole. Top with corn flakes and pour 1/2 c. melted margarine over top.

title: early american stew
directions: Brown ground round steak in a skillet in 2 tablespoons oil. Place all other ingredients in 1 gallon steel cooker.
Add browned meat and bring to full boil.
Turn down fire to simmer.
Cook 1 hour.
"Delicious."
Stir 4 times.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar; beat eggs and add with vanilla to cheese mixture.
Line muffin pan with cups and place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill half full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Add favorite topping.

title: beefy hash brown pizza
directions: In a bowl, combine the potatoes, soup, egg, salt and pepper. Spread mixture into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, cook the beef, onion and mushrooms until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in pizza sauce. Keep warm. Sprinkle 2 cups cheese over hot crust. Spread meat mixture over the top; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Mix together in a large bowl with all other ingredients.

title: mother's angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk and dry ingredients. Knead enough to hold together. Roll dough to 1/2-inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold in half. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs until creamy; mix in flour, oats, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, stirring until well blended. Shape or drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Turn to brown on all sides (may deep fry) or fry in 1/4-inch oil in skillet.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Stir until dissolved.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add cheese, stir until smooth.
Delicious when served with steamed broccoli, asparagus, brussel sprouts, cauliflower or over a baked potato. Enjoy!

title: lemon chicken
directions: Spray baking pan.
Mix flour, 1 teaspoon salt, paprika and 1/2 teaspoon poultry seasoning.
Coat chicken lightly.
Dip in melted margarine.
Put skin down in single layer.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Blend lemon juice, onion, pepper, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning.
After 25 minutes of cooking, turn chicken over and spoon sauce over each piece.
Return to oven and bake 25 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Fry bacon in a medium skillet over low heat until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Set bacon aside to drain.
Add green pepper, onion and potatoes to skillet; cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until the potatoes are browned.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes and stir until cheese melts.
Break eggs into skillet; cook over low heat, stirring gently, until done.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Break into bite size pieces.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: cool cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce, undrained pineapple, orange juice, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour into a large 9 x 12-inch casserole or two smaller ones.
Chill until firm.
I add the nuts with the rest of the ingredients. They will rise to the top and form a crisp crust.
To serve, cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves with sour cream or yogurt dressing.
Also may be served as a dessert with whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Saute (brown) in butter until brown. Mix soup, onion, seasoning in saucepan, gradually stir in water. Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Pour rice into shallow 2 qt. casserole dish.
Stir in all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of soup mixture, into rice.
Top with chicken and pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cove, and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a preheated 375 degree oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda. Combine butter, sugars and pudding mix in a large bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour gradually. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: green rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in Pyrex dish until mixture begins to boil, about 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage and vegetable soup
directions: Slit the sausage casing and crumble the meat in a large, heavy pot.
Cook it over low heat, breaking up the clumps of meat as it colors.
When the sausage has lost its rawness, pour off as much fat as you can, leaving the brown bits.
Add the onion and soften it, stirring.
Add the carrot, fennel or celery and garlic and cook them, stirring.
(If you have on hand a small amount of raw or cooked vegetables such as beans, broccoli, cabbage or spinach, chop and add them too.)
Add the tomatoes, stock, rice, corn and herbs; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or longer.
Before serving, discard the bay leaf, then salt and pepper to taste.
Serve the soup with good crusty bread.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: claude dodson's peach cobbler
directions: Pour the peaches into a large Pyrex dish.
Cut up margarine over peaches.
Sprinkle sugar over peaches.
Mix Bisquick and add water to make soft dough.
Spread evenly over peaches and sprinkle with a little cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: white fudge(opera fudge)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil slowly, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236° (or soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add flavoring; beat until the mixture loses its gloss, about 8 minutes.
Stir in cherries and walnuts.
Quickly put into greased tins (8 x 8-inch).
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Fill
jars
leaving
1/2-inch headspace.
Combine all ingredients and
bring to a boil.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Add lemon juice; pour over apples. Seal and cook 8 minutes in 10 pound pressure cooker.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix 2 kinds of corn with egg, salt and pepper.
Add flour until batter consistency.
Drop by spoonful in skillet of hot oil. Cook until brown on both sides.

title: potatoes and zucchini au gratin
directions: In medium saucepan, cook zucchini in water for 5 minutes. Drain; set apart.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and bouillon.
Gradually stir in milk; cook and stir until thick. Remove from heat.
Add cheese, pimiento and thyme; stir until cheese melts.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer 1/2 of potatoes, zucchini and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
Top with onions; bake 2 minutes longer.

title: roasted new potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes; drain and cool slightly.
Quarter potatoes with vegetable spray. Combine remaining ingredients.
Coat cut side of potatoes in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange on a coated cooking sheet and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: ripe tomato pickles
directions: Peel and cook all tomatoes until done.
Drain off only part of the juice.
Add all other ingredients and boil slowly until it thickens.
Pour into hot boiling jars.

title: apple betty pie
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with orange juice. For topping, combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
