Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly, then scatter over apples. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are done and topping is crisp and lightly browned.
Serve warm with pitcher of light cream or scoops of vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and thoroughly drain blueberries; toss berries with 2 Tbsp. flour.
Sift together remaining flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter, gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately in 3 parts.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan (9x5x3 inch).
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until done.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in 3-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
Bring to boil pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Add gelatin and congeal.
Whip the cream and beat congealed mixture with beater.
Fold in cream, cheese and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in orange rind and orange juice concentrate.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in pineapple, raisins and carrots.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice, add well drained pineapple.
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into crust & chill for 3 hours or more. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: barbara's ice cream topper
directions: In large skillet, mix butter, cinnamon, lemon juice, brown sugar, rum and cream de banana until hot and well mixed.
Add bananas and mix well until all hot, then pour over vanilla cream. Serve immediately.

title: fat-free apple coffeecake(a sure winner even for those who want to lose.)
directions: Spray a 9-inch round baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In a medium bowl, using a wire whisk or fork, thoroughly mix sugar and milk. Whisk in egg whites and corn syrup.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Arrange apples over top, overlapping to cover.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: wonton soup
directions: Combine ingredients to make filling.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling on each wonton wrapper, slightly off center.
Fold almost in half, pressing edges together, then fold in half again.
Pull the two corners together and stick them to each other with a little water.

title: italian grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cut up chicken to marinate 4 hours. Place on preheated grill.
Baste and turn every 15 minutes with 1/3 cup margarine and 1 teaspoon seasoning (usually 1 to 1 hour and 15 minutes).
On my grill, I have best luck if I light the right burner and bake it on the left side with the lid shut.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, melted shortening and yeast to dry mixture.
Roll thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Add jello, then add water. Let jell, then fold in Cool Whip, nuts and cheese.
Pour into pretty mold to set.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cream cheese and milk.
Add sugar, salt, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Blend well.
Makes 3 tablespoons.
Contains approximately 8 calories per teaspoon.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Peel, slice and arrange tomatoes in shallow dish.
Combine and mix well other ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Marinate in covered dish for 1 hour or more.
Serves 6.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together well and chill until ready to serve.

title: german pancakes
directions: Butter a frypan (Pam spray).
In blender, mix eggs until light color; add remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Bake in oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve with warmed syrup and powdered sugar.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Skin chicken; dip breasts in melted margarine and roll in crushed saltines; sprinkle with garlic salt Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Place in oblong pyrex pan. Bake slowly at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook onions, peppers and hamburger until brown; drain.
Add ketchup and 3 tablespoons of juice from olives.
Let meat mixture cook on low for about 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In 2-quart casserole dish put a layer of spaghetti and a layer of the meat mixture.
Pour soup over meat. Then, another layer of the spaghetti and meat mixture.
Place cheese on top.
Cut olives in slices and add to top of cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.

title: mexican corn pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture in a 10-inch pie plate that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cover and freeze until ready to use.
Reheat, covered and thawed, at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir in pecans.
Drop tablespoon size dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: cranberry-pecan upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange cranberries and nuts in the bottom of a greased 8-inch square pan.
Pour topping over fruit and nut mixture.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition. Pour batter over topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately invert onto serving platter; serve warm.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Variation:
Substitute 1 cup peeled and chopped apples for 1 cup cranberries.

title: chocolate mint sauce
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cook on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture is hot.
Stir until sauce is smooth or combine ingredients in small saucepan and stir over low heat until smooth.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in 1 bowl the apples, cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar. Mix in second bowl, the remaining ingredients. Mix batter well and in a greased and floured angel food cake pan, alternate batter and apples (1/2 the batter and 1/2 of the apples each time). Bake at 350° for an hour, then reduce heat to 325° and bake approximately 45 minutes more. Test with toothpick and if necessary, bake longer until toothpick comes out clean.

title: a-b-c casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine asparagus, water chestnuts, cheese and soup in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 6 x 9-inch dish. Dot with melted margarine; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: nut cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well. Chill. Shape dough into balls. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, until lightly browned on ungreased cookie sheet.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Cut onion in rings.
Dice bell pepper.
Mix with sugar, oil, vinegar, soup, salt and pepper. Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: giant snickerdoodle cookies
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, beat shortening with an electric mixer on medium to high speed 30 seconds.
Add 2 cups of sugar. Beat mixture until combined, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract or peel.
Add dry ingredient and buttermilk, alternately to creamed mixture, scraping down sides of bowl as necessary.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Meanwhile, combine 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Preheat oven at 375°. Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Use 1/4 cup measure or 1/4 cup ice cream scoop.
Roll each scoop of dough in sugar and cinnamon mixture to coat.
Place 3-inches apart on cookie sheet.
With palm of hand, gentle press down cookie to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until bottoms are light gold.
Transfer to rack. The cookies bake more evenly if you bake just one batch at a time. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: duffie's deer camp charcoal steak
directions: I prefer ribeye or T-bone steak for charcoaling.
Cook one large steak per person.
Rub
garlic salt on steak and then spread sauce on steak and let set for about 1 hour.
Sear both sides over hot charcoal fire, then cook for about 15 minutes.
Serve medium-rare for best taste.
Serve with baked potato and salad.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: Mix the flour, pecans and margarine; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: one pan pizza
directions: Grease a 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs in dish with a fork until batter is of uniform color (will be lumpy).
Stir in pepperoni, 1 cup cheese, green pepper, onion, oregano, basil and garlic salt.
Spread evenly.
Bake until top is light brown (about 30 minutes).
Spread with pizza sauce. Sprinkle with mushrooms and 1 cup cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted (about 1 to 2 minutes).

title: stove top play dough
directions: Boil water, oil and food coloring.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Let cool, then knead.
Store in covered container.

title: double up oreo ice cream
directions: Scald milk (heat until bubbles start to form).
Remove from heat; add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in half and half, vanilla and whipping cream.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Stir in cookies to chilled mixture.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: preacher's wives' peachy sunday special
directions: Add sugar slowly to beaten egg whites.
Add baking powder, vanilla and crackers.
Add nuts.
Place in a small loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Slice and top with peaches and cream.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread on serving platter.
Cover with jar of taco sauce. Add the following layers:
chopped lettuce, chopped onions, diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: main dish salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add kidney beans and salt. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Add beef and beans to salad mixture.
Toss again.
Garnish with chips, tomatoes or avocado.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream together butter or margarine with sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt in separate bowl. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Fold in peaches; stir in vanilla and almond. Bake for 75 to 80 minutes until done.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Mix together.
Put batter in an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Place filling in center of batter.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
You can use any kind of pie filling.

title: low-fat mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 325°, then sprinkle crushed onion ring snacks on top and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 1-quart casserole dish; mix drained broccoli in melted oleo.
Mix eggs, onion, mayonnaise and soup with broccoli. Sprinkle grated cheese on top; add cracker crumbs or stuffing mix. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°
or until firm or insert knife to see if it comes out clean.
Recipe may be halved.

title: black walnut squares
directions: Combine brown sugar, oil and water.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: rainbow punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, soften sherbet and frozen yogurt. Gradually blend in milk and juice with spoon until thoroughly blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 40 servings.

title: party chicken
directions: Do not add salt or any seasoning. Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon. Secure in the back with a tooth pick. Cover bottom of a greased baking dish with the chipped beef. Mix sour cream and soup until well blended. Pour over the chicken and with a spatula spread the mixture like you were frosting a cake. Refrigerate until ready to bake. Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours. No basting or attention needed while cooking.

title: quick cookie sheet bars
directions: Cook raisins and water together in a high saucepan; add margarine and soda to saucepan.
Stir until margarine melts.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and cinnamon; blend into saucepan.
Spread into greased large cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While warm, spread with powdered sugar or 4X sugar icing.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples.
Roll out four 7-inch circles of pie crust.
Place apple in center.
Fill center of apple with brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon and walnut mixture.
Place additional tablespoon of mixture in circle around apple.
Pull up pastry and pinch to seal.
Place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; drain juice from fruit thoroughly. Cut peaches in small pieces.
Add all fruit to milk mixture.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and chill for several hours. Delicious and easy to make.

title: sybil's old fashion raisin cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and milk and mix, then add raisins by stirring. (Raisins should be soaked in hot water overnight, then drained well.)
Start to bake in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: mountain pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder in mixing bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour this batter over butter or margarine which has been melted in pan.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: quick and easy barbecue chicken
directions: Mix pop and catsup in skillet.
Add meaty pieces of chicken and simmer 45 minutes or until sauce thickens and chicken is tender.
Delicious.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with potato masher or beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except pecans. Spoon sweet potato mixture into ungreased 1-quart casserole or souffle dish; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot throughout, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Mix well with spoon.
Place in a 10 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Place, in pan, in layers: bean dip, taco seasoning mixed with sour cream and mayonnaise, avocados with salt, pepper and lemon juice, tomatoes, onion, olives and cheese.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Mix well. Cool for 5 minutes in refrigerator.
Shape into balls and flatten.
Place on wax paper and chill for 30 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: When more than the minimum amount of water is used for cooking vegetables, never throw away the excess, but save this "Pot Liquor" as it is called.
Any vegetable (rutabaga, all greens and potatoes) may be cooked in this, with seasoning and extra water. Good with pone bread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into strips about 1 inch thick.
Place in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour together; sprinkle over potatoes.
Top with stick of butter.
Cover casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Clean and bake 4 medium size baking potatoes at 375° for approximately 45 minutes (until done).
Lay bacon on flat tray and cook in oven while potatoes are baking.
Saute butter, bacon, chives and onion when potatoes are close to being done.

title: vegetable hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil about 5 minutes or until tender. Add beef and cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain; add tomatoes, paste, salt, parsley and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in corn and peas.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place biscuits on top and bake at 350° or until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Add water to cover and soak overnight. Add rest of ingredients and bake at 300°
until done.
Check for liquid as the beans should be covered.

title: crab mayonnaise mexicaine(crab salad with jalapeno chilies)
directions: Pick over the crab to remove any bits of shell or cartilage. Put the mayonnaise, lime juice, chilies, coriander, chives and salt and pepper to taste into a bowl.
Add the crabmeat and toss lightly to blend without breaking up the crab lumps.

title: green chile souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chiles, in blender until frothy.
Stir in chopped chiles.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sourdough rolled biscuits
directions: Mix starter and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to starter
and oil.	Roll mixture on floured board.	Cut biscuits; place
on
greased	baking sheet and let rise for 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell (chilled). Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°, baking until knife comes out clean from center of pie, about 20 or 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add cocoa and eggs. Blend well. Add whipping cream. Pour into crumb crust.
Bake 40 minutes. Center may be soft but will set when cool. Cover when cool and chill overnight. Top pie with cherry or peach filling. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork parmesan
directions: Pound pork cutlets flat and cut into serving sizes.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs and brown.
Put in baking dish; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Top with shredded Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until tender.

title: drunken chicken-guatemala(pollo en pulque)
directions: Preheat oven to 375 F. In a medium saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic, saut for 3-5 minutes until tender.
Pour the onion/garlic mix into a large casserole dish. and place chicken on top of the mix.
Mix the beer, chicken broth, tomato, jalapeno, allspice, cinnamon stick and salt in a bowl, stir until blended.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake for 30 minutes in a covered dish.
Add potatoes and bake 30 more minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes or until it starts to brown on top.
Remove cinnamon stick after baking.
Serve with rice if desired.
Serves 8 hungry amigos.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into ball and roll in 1 cup pecans.
Chill until serving.
Garnish with fruit and serve with assorted crackers.

title: mac's house salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Whisking constantly, pour in steady stream 2 cups safflower oil.
Tear into bite-size pieces romaine, bibb and radicchio lettuce; add 1/2 pound sliced mushrooms, 2 cups grated Swiss cheese and the dressing.
Serves 12.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cream together well the cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Let jello cool in refrigerator until it starts to thicken.
Then add cream cheese mixture and whip together well.
Add crushed pineapple to cream cheese mixture.
Fold whipped evaporated milk into jello and cream cheese mixture, then spread 2/3 of butter and crumb mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put jello mixture on top of crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top; chill several hours.

title: strawberry omelet
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in omelet pan.
When cooked, add fresh sliced strawberries.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and fold omelet in half.
Remove from pan and sprinkle powdered sugar on top of omelet.
Serve at once.

title: my mother's orange slice cookies
directions: Dredge orange slices and nuts in small amount of flour.
Mix remaining ingredients and add orange slices and nuts, mixing well. Grease and slightly flour glass or metal baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts.
Beat well. Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not open oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layer of hamburger, potatoes, onions in 8 x 10 inch greased dish.
Pour tomatoes over mixture, top with cheese if desired. Bake in 350 degree over for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, butter and egg in medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.

title: york sensational brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix oleo, sugar and vanilla with fork.
Add eggs; stir until well blended. Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Save 2 cups of batter.
Spread remaining batter in pan.
Arrange patties in single layer over batter.
Add remaining 2 cups of batter over patties.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: homestead salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, dry mustard and vinegar until thick. Cool and pour over vegetables.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar and baking soda. Set aside.
In a saucepan, bring butter, cocoa and cola to a boil. Stir into dry ingredients. Stir in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Make icing.

title: pear sundaes
directions: Peel pears, leave on stems.
Simmer pears until semi-soft in the liquid, flavorings and sugar.
Cool.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Bring 1 cup water and sugar to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with 1/3 cup cold water; add to boiling mixture.
Simmer until thick and clear.
Add raspberry jello, stirring well.
Remove from fire.
Place fresh raspberries in baked pie shell (use a 9-inch pie shell).
Pour thickened filling over the berries.
Refrigerate pie for several hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream; garnish with several whole raspberries.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan you are baking in.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk; pour in pan of melted oleo.
Mix peaches and 1 cup sugar; bring to a boil or until sugar dissolves.
Pour in center of batter, but do not stir.
Bake until golden brown at 375°.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut hindquarter into 3 parts.
Cut away all gristle and fat. Slice meat against the grain into thin strips.
Soak strips for one hour in soy sauce (enough to cover strips).
After 1 hour, drain off soy sauce.
Lay strips on paper towel.
Salt with seasoned salt to taste.
Take strips off paper towel.
Put into dehydrator or oven.
Slow cook until dry on lowest temperature of oven.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Brown under broiler a few minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Thaw crabmeat overnight in refrigerator.
Boil shells until tender.
Cook peas as directed. Combine crabmeat, peas, mayonnaise, mustard and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Garnish with scallion (cut up).
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of mixture to shells. Enjoy.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Combine water with cranberries and boil about 1/2 hour or until berries begin to pop.
Add orange, raisins, pecans and sugar.
Reduce heat and cook on medium fire another half hour. Mixture will begin to thicken.
Pour into jelly jars.

title: over and under cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix according to directions. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, spread coconut and pecans. Pour cake batter on top.
Spread evenly in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Melt oleo and cream cheese; stir until well blended. Slowly add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corned beef and macaroni
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Lightly grease baking dish and pack in real firm.
Bake, covered, for 25 or 30 minutes at 375° to 400°.
The macaroni can be substituted with 4 medium white diced potatoes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients except tortillas.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot beef dish
directions: Brown onion and meat. Drain off grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into baking dish and cover with crushed taco chips or Fritos, then grated cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, egg and nuts with a fork.
Press into 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Mix with blender the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; pour over the pressed mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars or small squares.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix in cocoa.
Stir in vanilla, milk and 10x sugar.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: easiest ever biscuits
directions: Preparation: 5 minutes.
Cooking Time: 15 minutes. Temperature: 375°.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix ingredients together and keep in tight container to keep dry.
Put 2 teaspoons in a cup with hot water.

title: tapioca jello
directions: I use juice from strawberries as part of the 3 cups of water. Mix together.
Heat in a big pan to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes. Pour into bowl.
Cool a little; then add the fruit.

title: three fruit drink
directions: Put all in blender; process until smooth.
Yields 4 cups.

title: peanut patties
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil over medium flame.
Add peanuts.
Continue cooking until a little mixture becomes brittle when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir until boiling stops.
Add cream and beat until thick.
A few drops of red coloring will make it prettier.
Drop into patties on greased cookie sheet or pour into cookie sheet and cut into squares.

title: kapusta(polish cabbage soup)
directions: Drain soaking beans; cover with fresh water.
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile, fry bacon.
Cut in small bits.
Saute onion in bacon grease or other oil.
Add onion and bacon to cooked beans. Add tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar, molasses and spices.
You may need to add more water if soup is too thick.
Stir in cabbage. Cover pot and allow cabbage to steam.
Taste and adjust vinegar/sugar balance, garlic and pepper for a potent sweet and sour flavor.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: In large kettle, combine carrots, margarine, caraway seed and cook about 5 minutes until carrots are tender.

title: amaretto pecan pie surprise
directions: Beat cream cheese and 2 tablespoons Amaretto, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg.
Spread in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture, then lightly press into cream cheese. Combine 3 eggs, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and Amaretto.
Beat until well blended; pour over pecans.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter and pour in 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter. Sprinkle coconut evenly over graham cracker crumbs. Next, evenly spread chocolate chips, then layer the butterscotch chips. Pour the condensed milk evenly over pan. Spread chopped walnuts over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hester's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
When done, cool and add salt, chopped eggs, mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Now pour the vinegar solution over potatoes and stir lightly.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling, salted water about 5 minutes.
Remove from water and set aside.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients and 1/2 of nuts.
Mix well and press into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Brush top with slightly beaten whites and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered bowl.
Use as desired.
Fill tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with sugar/or cinnamon before baking.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Dough keeps in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Mix cider and other ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: death by chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in rectangular pan.
Cool cake, then poke holes with fork across cake.
Pour Kahlua over cake.
Crush candy bars.
Prepare mousse according to directions on box.
In a deep glass bowl or trifle dish, layer slices of cake, mousse, candy and cream.
Repeat, ending with cream.
Sprinkle some crumbled candy on top.
Chill overnight.

title: sunday pork roast
directions: Place roast or chops (seasoned to taste) in Dutch oven.
Top with apple slices, onion and sauerkraut. Cover and place in preheated 300° oven before leaving for Sunday school.
After church (approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours), remove from oven and enjoy.
(Good served with baked sweet potatoes.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease a 12 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish and layer 1/2 the squash.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolk until thick; stir in sour cream and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into yolks.
Layer this mixture over squash; add layer of onions.
Layer remaining squash, cheese and bacon.
Add bread crumbs on top and paprika, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: paradise salad
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 1/2 cups water; add apples.
Chill until firm.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in reserved juice; add cream cheese.
Pour over firm cherry gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lime gelatin in remaining water.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour over firm lemon gelatin; chill until firm.
Servings: 15.

title: piccalilli
directions: Simmer 2 to 3 hours until mixture "cooks down".
Makes 6 1/2 pints.
Has a wonderful odor while cooking.
Good to use on meats and turnip salad!

title: country brunch
directions: Cook bacon in 10 to 12-inch skillet until crisp; remove from skillet.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add green pepper, onion, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove cover.
Lift mixture with pancake turner to thoroughly turn and mix potatoes.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes; thoroughly mix potatoes again.
Make 6 indentions in potato mixture; break egg into each indention.
Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are almost set (about 3 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese and crumble bacon over all.
Cook until eggs are done, about 5 minutes.

title: kate's vegetable soup
directions: My mom combines all of this and simmers it all day in a large soup pot.
The longer it simmers, the better it is.

title: fort knox pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Press mixture into a 9-inch pie plate pressing to form sides for high rim.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage and garlic in fry pan.
Add beans, molasses and spices to taste.
Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hours.
Cook rice. Mix together or put rice on top of beans.
Serve with corn bread.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Store in a tightly covered jar.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter large baking pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Mix box cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop in dollops over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool; cut in squares from pan.

title: chocolate peanut treats
directions: In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs and butter; mix well. Stir in sugar and peanut butter. Press into a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: sauce for roast pork
directions: Combine, heat and simmer for several minutes.
Delicious served with an outdoor pig roast.

title: virgin mary
directions: Fill a large glass with crushed ice.
Add tomato juice to fill. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, horseradish (optional), salt and pepper. Add celery stick as a stirrer and garnish.

title: apple walnut cheesecake
directions: Mix
cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until combined.
Pour into graham cracker crumb lined spring-form
pan.
Top
with
apples
which
have
been microwaved for 3 minutes or until soft.
Sprinkle walnuts over apples.
Top with
a
mixture
of cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar. Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into deep hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar, egg whites, salt and cinnamon.
Beat until stiff. Fold nuts into meringue.
Melt butter on cookie sheet.
Spread nuts on cookie sheet and bake.
Stir well every 10 minutes.

title: mint chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Scald milk until bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in half and half, vanilla and whipping cream.
Add peppermint extract and green food coloring.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Freeze as directed.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee, sugar and water in saucepan; bring to boil and simmer for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine milk, coffee mix and ice cream.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil, peel and chill shrimp.
Boil potatoes and dice.

title: "best ever" pudding
directions: Raisins may be substituted for dates.

title: praline ice cream pudding pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and nuts in small saucepan. Heat over medium heat until butter is melted. Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 5 minutes or until bubbly. Cool on wire rack.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin
in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Slice strawberries, reserving a few for garnish, if desired, and sprinkle with sugar.
Blend whipped topping
into
gelatin;
then
fold
in cake cubes and strawberries.
Spoon into 10-inch tube pan or 13 x 9-inch cake pan; chill
until
firm,
about
hours.
Unmold or cut into squares.
Garnish
with
additional
whipped
topping
and the reserved strawberries.
Makes 10 cups or 12 to 15 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and mix well.
Store in a tight container. To serve, spoon 3 heaping tablespoonfuls into a mug and add 3/4 cup boiling water; stir.

title: pumpkin tart
directions: Mix and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine, melted.
Beat together 2 eggs, cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low-fat spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours to let flavors blend.
Stir before serving.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Layer zucchini in 8-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter, add 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese until soft.
Add sour cream and seasoning.
Heat until all are blended.
Pour over squash. Combine bread crumbs and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese; sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge nut bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover tops of baked bars with halved marshmallows. Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Squish marshmallows down so as to cover bars evenly.
Cool.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: betty's brownies
directions: Melt the oleo and chocolate.
Cool.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add flour mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot potato-n-sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat until bacon is crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Add sugar, flour and celery seed.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Add enough water to sauerkraut liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir sauerkraut liquid and vinegar into mixture in skillet; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring frequently.
Add potatoes, sauerkraut, celery and green onions; stir gently.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift remaining ingredients and add.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexicanos
directions: Season meat with salt.
Shape into 6 patties, then saute to desired doneness.
Meanwhile, slice and toast corn-bread squares. Serve one patty on each square.
Pour hot chili or baked beans over all.
Nice with tomato soup.

title: orange salad
directions: Peel oranges and combine with celery and nuts.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Place on crisp lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: priscilla's meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll into balls.
Place in glass dish; cook at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Blend well and refrigerate. Score cucumbers down sides with a fork and slice. Spread a layer of cream cheese mixture on a slice of rye bread and top with a cucumber slice.
Refrigerate.
Mix cream cheese and Ranch mix 8 to 24 hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Roll in 1 cup pecans into shape of a ball.

title: sis' butter ball recipe
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt. Cream the butter and vanilla together.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts; again mix well.
Roll in little balls and place on nonstick cookie sheet or lightly greased regular cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° to 325° oven.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package.
Allow to cool.
Mix all ingredients except 1/3 of Cool Whip.
Place in pie crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: soft chocolate topping(frosting)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk and chocolate. Bring mixture to full boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter; stir until melted and frosting is smooth.
While warm, spread on the cake.

title: lynda's applesauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: vegeburger roast
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grape jelly
directions: Heat grapes, then run them through a colander to remove juice. Add 1 cup of water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 7 cups of sugar and Certo.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: delicious rice krispies cookies
directions: Blend oleo and oil; cream in sugar and add egg and flavoring. Beat well; sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Can add M&M's, peanuts or chocolate or butterscotch chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven or until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: crock-pot or seven hour oven stew
directions: Place all ingredient in crock-pot and cook all day on low or place in large roaster and bake at 250° for 7 to 8 hours.
Serve with make ahead salad, crusty bread and dessert.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Simmer combined ingredients 20 minutes or so. Add green pepper during last 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
(Good, and very easy!)

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat ball garden skillet
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 325°.
Cook the onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender, but not brown.
Combine beef, flour, salt, milk and egg.
Beat thoroughly until light and fluffy. Add cooked onion and form into 1-inch balls.
Brown balls lightly in 1 tablespoon butter in 350° skillet.
Push meat balls to one side.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour into fat in skillet; add broth and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions to skillet.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Pour boiling water over frozen peas if desired.
Add peas to skillet; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
May be served directly from skillet.

title: coconut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add shortening, milk, beaten egg and coconut.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot peppers
directions: Make sauce and boil.
Add pepper rings and boil 10 minutes. Pack in jars and fill with sauce.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: easy anginetti cream puffs
directions: Prepare Anginetti by slicing off tops.
Hold aside.

Drain crushed pineapple, leaving a little juice. Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl, about 1 minute, at medium speed. Add crushed pineapple and blend all 3 ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling from tablespoon onto bottom layer of cookies; replace tops.
Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.
(Filling should be enough to fill all or most of the cookies in this package.)

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and add to sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixed.
Add flour, chips, coconut, nuts and vanilla and mix well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°
for 35 minutes,
just until set.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: 4 layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix and pat firmly in a 13 x 15-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: campfire dinner
directions: Take a double layer of heavy aluminum foil; place all ingredients on foil.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper. Close foil, making sure that all edges are sealed.
Place on hot coals in campfire, or place on wire grate close to fire.
Will take about 45 minutes to cook.

title: sacher bites
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and unsweetened chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Spread the preserves over top of cookies in baking pan.
Cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise, to make 4 rectangles.
Loosen edges.
Remove from pan. Stack 2 rectangles, preserves side up.
Trim off edges, if necessary.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars and place on wire rack covered with wax paper.
Repeat with remaining stacked rectangles. In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Drizzle some chocolate over top of each bar.
Chill to harden chocolate. Makes 40.

title: oat cake
directions: Bake in one layer cake pan for 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, oleo and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture. Stir until blended.
Pour batter onto preheated grids of lightly greased waffle iron.
Bake about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 1 cup baking mix and the powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Bake about 10 minutes or until light brown.
Mix remaining ingredients except glaze.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake about 25 minutes or until set and golden brown.
While warm, loosen edges from sides of pan.
Spread with glaze.
Cool completely.
Cut into about 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: diabetic strawberry smoothie
directions: Combine yogurt, milk and Equal in blender. With blender running, add strawberries, a few at a time, through opening in lid. Blend until smooth. Add ice cubes, one at a time, blending until slushy. Makes 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order:
lettuce, cauliflower, onion, pepper and peas. Mix mayonnaise, Ranch dressing, sugar and sour cream.
Top layered vegetables with dressing made by mixing mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and dry Ranch dressing, sealing on all edges.
Add Cheddar cheese and bacon bits as toppings.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until the mixture coats a spoon. Cool; strain and add heavy cream and vanilla.
Freeze.
Makes 3 pints.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Freeze.

title: chicken "quickie"
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving some chow mein noodles to sprinkle on top.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (or until bubbly).

title: lo-cal white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour and hot water.
Beat eggs until whites are very stiff.
Fold in baking powder and egg whites.
Bake in cake pan until done by checking with toothpick.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and cake mix.
Add and mix milk, vegetable oil and eggs.
Add half mixture of frozen strawberries, coconut and chopped nuts.
Use other half of fruit and nut mixture, 1 stick butter and 1 box confectioners sugar to ice cake.
Bake in 3 paper lined pans, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the soft shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart (they spread a lot).
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft, at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.) Makes 5 dozen.

title: shoestring apple pies
directions: Mix all together.
Put into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top; bake at 325° until done.
Test like a custard pie.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to mixture. Add chocolate chips and nuts last.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: chicken scaloppini a la pizzaola
directions: In large frypan, melt butter.
Add mushrooms and saute lightly 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
In same butter, saute chicken, seasoned with salt and pepper, for about 5 minutes. Remove from pan; drain liquid.
Add olive oil, onion and garlic; saute for 3 minutes.
Cut up tomatoes.
Add with tomato puree, water and paste, oregano, basil and bay leaf.
Return chicken to pan and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Add wine, cheese, olives and mushrooms; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with cooked pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy orange chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine water, onion, orange concentrate, catsup, garlic, cinnamon, Tabasco pepper sauce and salt; mix well. Place chicken in large shallow dish or plastic bag; add marinade. Cover; refrigerate at least 4 to 6 hours.
Turn chicken occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade; place on grill 4 to 5-inches from source of heat.
Grill 25 to 30 minutes or until done; turn frequently and brush each time with marinade.
Heat any remaining marinade to a boil and serve with chicken.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Using a fork, beat all ingredients in the order in which they are listed.
Do not overbeat or overbake.
Makes 12 muffins.
For best results, use cupcake liners.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil or butter; stir only until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.

title: heavenly fried rice
directions: Cook the rice a day ahead and allow to get cold. Brown the bacon, remove from grease and crumble.
Add the eggs, rice and scallions to the bacon grease.
Add the leftover meat and soy sauce.
Saute until rice is as brown as you like.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt; shape into 50 small meatballs (1/2-inch).
Place in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Broil until browned; turn once.
Spoon off fat. Meanwhile in saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs. Cover; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jam ripple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour an 8 inch spring form pan.
In a large bowl stir together flour and
sugar. Stir in baking powder, salt, and nutmeg.
In a small bowl beat the egg, milk, and melted butter together.
Make a well in the flour mixture and then pour in the egg mixture, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Spread batter into the prepared spring form pan.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa; add alternately with vanilla and food color to creamed mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar; add with buttermilk to batter.
Do not beat. Pour into two (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done (25 to 30 minutes might do it).

title: irish raisin bread
directions: Place vinegar in 3-cup mixing bowl.
Add enough milk to make 2 cups.
In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add margarine, seed and raisins.
Mix together lightly with fork.
Add milk mixture, stirring with a fork, but do not overmix; this is important.
Put batter into greased loaf pan or 8-inch cake pan.
Pour melted margarine over top; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Lower to 350° and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until it tests done.

title: strawberries elizabeth
directions: Fill tall glasses with hot Amaretto.
Add large spoonful of whipping cream, then add chocolate sauce or fudge.
Bottoms up!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix eggs, water and oil together.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cut sour cream into dry mixture, then mix in the wet ones. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil, eggs and milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour. Remove from pan and pour topping over the top of the warm cake.

title: new year's day soup
directions: Wash beans and soak 24 hours.
Drain.
In large Dutch oven, add beans, water, ham, onion, garlic and tomatoes.
Cover and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add tomatoes with chilies.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve cornbread.
Serve generously with love and affection.
Sure to bring you health and prosperity for the new year.

title: butterscotch (or chocolate) supreme
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, melted margarine and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°; cool.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Place buttered side down in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 2 cheeses and sprinkle with chiles.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 4 hours. Uncover and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix the flour, butter and walnuts.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel
potato
and
boil until soft.
Drain; run through ricer. Cool
slightly.
Add vanilla and enough powdered sugar to make pie
dough
consistency.
Roll out between wax paper. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll;
slice.

title: easy jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of two 8-inch cake pans. Line bottom of pans with wax paper.
Grease and flour waxed paper and sides of pans.	Mix cake by directions on box.	Add jam, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks.
Remove wax paper and cool completely.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Make crust by mixing pretzels, pecans, butter and sugar. Press mixture into 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake for 8 - 10 minutes, remove from oven and let cool. Mix cream cheese, cool whip and powdered sugar. Spread on cooled crust and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Mix boiling water and Jello; add strawberries to Jello, stir well and pour on top of cream cheese. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Fry ribs on all sides until brown in shortening.
Put them in a roaster.
Mix flour, mustard, salt, pepper, cloves, ketchup, water and pickle juice together.
Slice or dice onion over ribs, them pour everything over ribs and onions.
Cook until the ribs are tender about 1 hour at 275°.
Cook slowly.
Be careful not too cook dry.

title: spectacular spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large skillet, season ground beef with seasoned salt, black pepper and garlic powder.
Cook, drain and set aside. (Form meatballs before cooking, if desired.)

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Puree bananas (1 cup).
Cream together the butter and sugars. Beat in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; beat dry ingredients into banana mixture.
Fold in peanut butter chips, nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes until brown. Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat eggs; mix into sugar.
Mix dry ingredients with sugar, shortening and eggs, then add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs, salt and pumpkin pie spice. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour mixture into glass pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Pour 1 cup melted butter on cake mix.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients;
blend margarine and lard into dry ingredients as you
would
for
pie
crust.
Add currants. Make a well in the
center;
add beaten eggs and milk to well. Form a ball of dough.
When
all
the dough has formed and the bowl is clean, break
off
smaller pieces and roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut in circles
and
fry
on
electric
griddle at 300°.
Fry on one side
for
3 minutes, then flip once and fry until brown. Cool on racks.
Bag in plastic.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add flavoring and sugar.
Add ice water.
Add flour.
Add nut meats.
Make into small finger rolls.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: Cook beef until browned and drain off grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and heat thoroughly.

title: coffee cake
directions: Prepare batter by blending all ingredients.
Mix well.

title: rolls
directions: Put sugar, salt and shortening in bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Soak yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add well beaten egg to yeast mixture.
When other bowl is cool, add yeast and egg.
Then add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix, then put in refrigerator.
Let rise. Let stand out about 10 minutes.
Make into buns and let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 15 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Brown sausage.
Remove from skillet and saute celery and onion.
In large bowl, combine soups and milk.
Fold in rice, sausage, celery, onion and croutons.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown hamburg. Take out of skillet and put onions in to saute. Put rest of ingredients in baking dish and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg balls
directions: Chop the hard-boiled eggs finely.
Mix all ingredients until creamy. Shape into small balls. Chill
well before serving. Yields 60 balls.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and confectioners sugar.
Melt margarine and add to graham cracker mixture.
Mix together well and press 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13 -inch pan.
Set remainder aside. After preparing Dream Whip according to directions on package, add cream cheese and beat together until well blended.
Spread 1/2 of Dream Whip mixture over graham crackers in pan.
Set remainder aside.
Spread blueberries on Dream Whip mixture.
Spread remainder of Dream Whip mixture over blueberries.
Sprinkle remainder of graham cracker mixture over Dream Whip mixture and press lightly.
Cover.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: barbecue beans for a crowd
directions: In a 5
quart
Dutch
oven,
add the above ingredients. Bring to a boil,
then lower heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring often.

title: honey corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, biscuit mix and baking powder in a large bowl. Add milk, eggs, honey and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into an 8-inch square microwave-proof baking dish.
Cook on 50 for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish if bread seems to be rising unevenly.
Cook on High 2 to 4 minutes or until bread tests done.
Remove from microwave and let stand 5 minutes. Serve warm.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 20 brownies.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in bag.
Set aside.
Mix pudding.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with crushed Oreo cookies, reserving about a handful.
Pour pudding mixture on top of crushed cookies.
Work fast so that pudding mixture will still be liquidy in order to soften cookies.

title: dilled pickled okra
directions: Use small, tender pods of okra, cut with as much stem as possible.
Wash and drain.
Prick okra and pack into clean jars. Place a small bunch of green dill in each jar with the okra.
Boil water, vinegar and salt together until salt is dissolved.
Fill jars with boiling hot brine.
Put on cap, screwing the band firmly tight.
Process jars 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in hot milk, pour over bread crumbs, mix well. Add to squash.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May cover top with buttered crumbs.

title: eric's microwave hot fudge topping
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 2-cup glass bowl.
Stir in water.
Cook on Full power 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds with whisk.
Blend in butter.
Cook on Full power 30 to 45 seconds at a time, whisking as you go, until thick.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 1 cup topping.
Sauce thickens quickly near the end.

title: asparagus and radish salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Add the radish slices and marinate for 3 hours.
Place the asparagus on the salad greens.
Drain the radishes, keeping the marinade.
Place the radishes on the asparagus and serve with the marinade.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add cream cheese. Stir until melted. Soften gelatin in cold water. Stir into pineapple mixture. Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Pour into baking dish or salad bowl.

title: caramel (for apples)
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cook slowly, stirring constantly to 230° or to stiff ball stage.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add to liquids.
Use amount of water to make batter that will stay on fish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, white and brown sugar and egg.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add slowly and mix.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine concentrates and water; add grenadine.
Chill thoroughly.
Pour mixture into large punch bowl; add ice.
Slowly add carbonated beverage.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: wet-bottom molasses cake
directions: Combine the flour and baking soda in a large bowl.
Stir oil, molasses and hot water in small bowl.
Mix well.
Add to flour mixture in large bowl and stir until thoroughly combined.
Place the batter in a lightly oiled 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: creamed breast of chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts in 1 stick of margarine for 1 hour at 350°.
Dice.
Dice and saute onion in 1 stick of margarine.
Add soups, undiluted.
Add diced chicken and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve in baked party pie shells.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Halve zucchini.
Clean out pulp and seeds. Brush zucchini with melted butter.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place cut side down in shallow baking pan.
Add a little water and cover with foil.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes, until almost tender.
While zucchini bakes, brown meats.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add remainder of ingredients to the meat mixture.
Turn zucchini halves hollow side up.
Spoon mixture into zucchini.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
When almost done, top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put skinless, boneless breasts in glass casserole.
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; cook 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; put drained pineapple chunks and green pepper slices in; bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole dish, put chicken.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Mix together stuffing mix and about 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Spread over other mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix sweet milk, sugar and Crisco together.
Put on stove and let come to a boil.
Take off and cool.
Add one yeast cake.
When yeast has dissolved, add 4 cups of flour.
Set in warm place.
Let rise until it doubles.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Melt cream cheese, butter and milk together.
Add green chilies and corn.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with enchilada casserole and Mexican cornbread.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Serve on hot biscuits or toast and butter.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix and make into small meatballs. Brown in 2 tablespoons oil.

title: pear relish
directions: Put on stove and cook on medium heat until done.
Put in jars and seal.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Take 1/4 cup sugar and brown it.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Let cook to a thick syrup.
Add 2 1/4 cups sugar, the sweet cream, butter, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cook to 238° to 240°, or until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water. Take off; put in cool water.
When cool, beat until thick.
If too thick, you can add a little water or milk.
Use recipe for 1, 2, 3 or 4 layers.

title: salt dough
directions: For craft or ornaments.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saut bell pepper, onion and celery in butter until tender. Add crawfish tails, green onions, parsley and seasonings. Thicken with cornstarch if needed. Place half of pie crust in pan and fill with cooled mixture. Place top crust on pie. Cut two 1-inch long slits in top crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Then lower temperature to 375° and bake for 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Slice 2 lemons thinly.
Squeeze juice from other 2 lemons.
Combine all ingredients with shrimp in Pyrex dish. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add sour cream.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip (save the other half for top).
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas.
Makes 1 large pudding.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Run the cabbage, bell peppers and onions through a food chopper.
Pour the pickling salt over this mixture.
Mix well and let stand for two hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on package and bake.
Punch holes in top.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk and coconut cream while hot.
Cool completely.
Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut.
Chill overnight or a day.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix package.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Don't let cake cool completely.
Poke holes all over cake top and before cake is cool, drizzle Eagle Brand milk over top. Use end of a wooden spoon to make holes in cake (if holes are too small, milk will not go through).
After cake is completely cooled, spread with caramel topping using the whole jar.
Spread Cool Whip on top of caramel topping.
Sprinkle Heath bars on top of Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: 3 way bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add other ingredients.
Chill for a few hours.

title: country's chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, thoroughly blend sugar and cocoa powder.
Add vanilla and salt and blend well.
Blend in margarine.
Add eggs and evaporated milk and blend well.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
The pie will puff up and the top will crack when it is done.
Makes 1 (9 or 10-inch) pie.

title: six layer dinner
directions: In a 3 quart casserole dish-layer potatoes, corn, onions and ground beef, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until tender.
Serves 6 people.

title: flourless fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In large bowl, combine pecans, walnuts, dates, pineapple, cherries, condensed milk and coconut.
Mix with hands.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake until no milk oozes out of cake when pressed with finger, about 1 1/2 hours.
Decorate with reserved pecans and cherries, if desired.
Let cool.
Turn out on plastic wrap and wrap snugly, then wrap snugly in foil.
Store in refrigerator or freezer about 1 month before serving.
Makes one 10-inch tube cake.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Grease and flour large cookie sheet.
Cream brown sugar and margarine with eggs.
Add hot coffee; stir well.
Add dry ingredients (flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda).
Pour batter into large, greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with choice of chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, add 12 eggs, one at a time, cream well after each addition.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Add 5 cups of flour, one at a time, add milk and beat well.
Save 1 cup flour for fruit mixture.
Chop fruit and put into large bowl, add remaining 1 cup flour, mix well.
Pour batter over this mixture.
Line pans with foil and grease.
Use 2 tube pans or 1 tube pan and small pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: persimmon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange and lemon juices. Chill until syrupy.
Add persimmon pulp and chill until firm. Serve on a slice of pineapple.

title: crispy oven potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Layer potatoes in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, brushing each layer with butter mixture.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: ginger shortbread cookies
directions: In medium bowl, whisk flour with ground ginger and salt.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Using a wooden spoon, gradually beat in the dry ingredients.
Stir in the crystallized ginger until well distributed.
Gather dough into ball.
Cut into quarters and pat into 4 individual balls.
Wrap each ball in wax paper and refrigerate 1 hour until firm.
Roll out on lightly floured board. Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on 2 ungreased cookie sheets one inch apart.
Bake at 325°.
After 6 minutes switch cookie sheets in oven.
Bake until golden.
Remove to wire rack.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir over heat until mixture dissolves.
Cook without stirring until syrup reaches light crack stage (270°).
Pour syrup slowly over egg whites. Beat constantly until mixture holds its shape.
Add chopped nuts, candied cherries and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto buttered sheet.
Garnish with candied cherry halves.

title: swiss steak
directions: Using mallet, pound flour into both sides of steak.
Saute steak in butter in large skillet over high heat.
Quickly brown both sides.
Place steak in large pot.
Arrange vegetables on steak.
Add skillet drippings, consomme and seasonings.
Simmer, tightly covered, for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Serve over rice or broad noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Cook until thick, then add rest of milk to make one gallon.

title: peanut butter, marshmallow, krispie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare and bake brownies following package directions.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows on hot brownies; return to oven. Bake 3 minutes longer.

title: my favorite pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients with water to egg mixture. Bake in 3 loaf pans in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or in 6 tea size loaf pans about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Combine sifted flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apple-sugar mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Frost if desired with lemon frosting.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, 7-Up and flavoring.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easiest meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs with a fork in a large bowl.
Mix in the tomato paste, onions, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, shoyu sauce, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream; mix with pumpkin and honey.
Add spices and pecans. Mix together well in large mixing bowl.
Pour into shell; freeze overnight.
Set out ten minutes before cutting.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Stir together the gelatin and boiling water to dissolve.
Add cold water.
Chill until partly thickened.
Cut oranges into wedges and remove seeds.
Don't peel.
Put oranges and cranberries through a food chopper or chop in blender.
Add sugar and celery. Add to partly thickened gelatin mixture. Turn into a mold.
Chill until firm, 3 hours or more.
Makes 12 servings.

title: death by chocolate(yield: 8 - 10 servings)
directions: 1. Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese, then sprinkle crushed corn chips around edge.

title: ken's goulash
directions: Cook green pepper until tender.
Add hamburger and remaining ingredients, except macaroni.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook macaroni for 12 minutes; add to hamburger mixture.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat the butter until creamy, gradually beating in the lemon juice and rind. Serve with meat or fish.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until solid.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut in your favorite shapes. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may sprinkle with colored sugar before baking or frost with powdered sugar frosting when cool.

title: tuscan-style spelt rotini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, steam spinach in a large saucepan, covered, until wilted.
Drain and squeeze out moisture.
Chop finely, then crumble with fingers to separate chopped leaves.

title: turkey cookies
directions: No baking!
Kids can help!
Take one Oreo and put icing on the back of one side.
Push 1 fudge-striped cookie (stripes pointing up) against it.
Spread icing on the bottom of a gum drop and place on top of the Oreo.
Dip the large end of the candy corn in the icing and put on the front side of the gum drop (pointing down). You and the kids finish treating yourself on the extra goodies.

title: cheezy hash browns
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350°
for about 1 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat together and bake in unbaked pie shell 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups hot water.
Add bananas, strawberries and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into flat dish and let congeal (about 30 minutes).
Spread sour cream and then pour remaining mixture on top.
Put in refrigerator.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Thoroughly blend yogurt, horseradish and orange juice.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Serve with beef or seafood.
Yields 1/4 cup.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Mix cereal, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon into medium size muffin tins with only bottoms greased.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (18 to 22 minutes).
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Melt 3/4 stick Parkay.
Add sugar, eggs, cream or milk and sweet potatoes (drained).
Mix in blender.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with mixture of Parkay, brown sugar, corn flakes and chopped nuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This is very special!!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Mix salt, soda and cream of tartar into flour. Blend into creamed mixture. Take balls the size of walnut. Roll until round.
Roll in granulated sugar. Flatten with glass dipped in water, then in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown on edges. Remove from baking sheet at soon as done. (I use Pam in the pan.
These are delicate and burn easily.)

title: chicken casserole 5
directions: Mix butter with stuffing.
You may add broth from chicken. Press into casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and onion over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Pour over stuffing mix and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough in rounds and press on round pizza pan. Bake according to package.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in a large pot 20 to 25 minutes until tender; drain and return potatoes to pot. Add butter and mash. Stir in 1 1/4 cups cheese, milk, sour cream and eggs until blended. Then add 3/4 cup scallions, 1/2 the crumbled bacon, salt and pepper. Spoon into a 3-quart baking dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining scallions.

title: margaret's potatoes
directions: Heat butter and soup in saucepan.
When it is thoroughly heated, add the sour cream.
Remove from heat and add onions and cheese.
Put the potatoes in a 2-quart buttered baking dish and gently mix in the soup mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and chopped mushrooms.
Cook for awhile.
Cook noodles.
Put in layers in a 13 x 9-inch pan:
noodles, then meat sauce, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Boil 3 cups sugar, syrup and hot water until spins thread. Pour into beaten egg whites while continuing to beat.
Cook 1 1/2 cups sugar and 3/4 cup water until spins a thread.
Pour into mixture and beat to peaks.
Cool completely.
Knead with confectioners sugar until right consistency.
Roll out; spread with peanut butter.
Roll, chill and slice.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix together day ahead and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, walnuts, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Beat brown sugar, egg whites, oil, puree and vanilla until blended. Reduce speed on mixer to low and add flour mixture. Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes in 375° oven.

title: english toffee (heath bars)
directions: Mix
together
butter and brown sugar and cook until it boils. Boil slowly for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased
9	x
12-inch
Pyrex
dish or container.
