Put a couple of	Hershey bars on top and spread over entire mixture or chocolate
chips
can be used.
You can also put in chopped nuts before pouring into pan, if desired.

title: ethel's sugar cookies
directions: Sprinkle with sugar before baking.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Place in pan and cook on low heat, stirring until sugar has dissolved.
When it bubbles, cook at least 15 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add 1 small package strawberry jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool; put in jars.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 2 (12 ounce) jars or 1 (18 ounce) jar.

title: mr. rapp's luncheon fillet of beef
directions: Take a small, thick fillet beef and brown in a small amount of butter for about 7 or 8 minutes on each side over high heat.
This is best done in a heavy iron skillet.
Set aside and add to skillet about 3-1/2 tablespoons of sour cream and about 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Mix with pan juices then pour 1/2 over beef.
Let cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold next day for lunch.
Use other half of heated sauce to pour over top.
Serve with German fried potatoes and a small salad.

title: beets and horseradish
directions: Finely grate beets after draining liquid.
Add horseradish to taste.
Refrigerate.
Excellent with ham.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: magic cookie bars(serves 16)
directions: Put oleo in 8 x 12 Pyrex dish; sprinkle other ingredients over it. (Crumbs first, milk last.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hand grenade dip(10 second delay)
directions: In a blender, place tuna, mayonnaise and onion.
Process until smooth. Add jalapeno peppers and cilantro, processing until chopped fine. Blend in white pepper. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve cold with chips or vegetables.
Tortilla chips are best.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in sealed container (jar). When ready to enjoy, spoon approximately 2 teaspoons of mixture into cup and add boiling water.

title: veal marsala (4)
directions: Rub veal with garlic and dredge with seasoned flour.
Heat frying pan (very hot).
Melt butter; heat to sizzle.
Brown veal on both sides.
Add Marsala; cook 1 minute, basting continuously. Keep heat high.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop all vegetables very small.
Mix with cooled spaghetti and add dressing.
Allow to marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
You may also add any other vegetables, such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots or zucchini.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of soup and remaining ingredients. Shape firmly into loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each time.
Add flour alternately with milk, ending with flour.
Add flavoring, nuts and cherries.
(Cherries should be well drained and rolled in flour.)
Bake in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Cake should start in cold oven.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.In a medium bowl, combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise. Place layer of broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish. Add a layer of cheese. Pour sauce on top. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used. Top with stuffing mix. Sprinkle butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour and salt in a bowl and set aside. In a separate bowl, mix butter, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Add remaining sugar and eggs and beat. Continue to beat on low speed while slowly pouring in flour mixture. Chill thoroughly. Roll dough to 1/8 to 1/4 inch thickness on a well floured surface and cut with cookie cutters. Place cookies on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400 degrees. Let cookies cool and decorate with icing or as desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put into 2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "jogging in the jug"
directions: Save 1 cup of water and mix with the honey.
Boil honey in water.
Add vinegar to juice; don't add vinegar to honey and water. Mix all together and you have "Jogging in the Jug."

title: pork chop one dish meal
directions: Cook rice and drain.
In heavy pan with small amount of cooking oil, brown pork chops.
Do not overcook.
Salt and pepper. Place in baking dish.
On each, put large tablespoon of rice, slice of tomato, onion and bell pepper.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs with milk; beat like scrambled eggs.
Add bacon (pepper to taste).
Spread 2 tablespoons (or more) of salsa over crust.
Pour egg mixture very carefully over the salsa and crust.
Spread cheese over pizza.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until center is set (if knife comes out clean).

title: good apple pie
directions: Cut up enough apples to fill 1 pie shell.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and flour.
Put this over apples.
Top that with 1 stick of butter, sliced.
Top with second pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: rizogalo(greek rice pudding)
directions: Place rice, sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Do not stir. Cover and heat over medium low heat until pot begins to steam, about 20 minutes (watch so that it does not boil over).
Uncover pan, stir and lower flame to simmer.
Cover loosely and cook for 45 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring frequently.
Mix beaten eggs with evaporated milk and gradually add to rice during the last 5 minutes of cooking.
(Stir constantly until mixture thickens, but do not let it boil.)
Ladle into serving dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put apple slices in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle water over apples.

Mix flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon with a fork until crumbly. Stir in butterscotch chips. Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake, uncovered, until topping is light golden brown and apples are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend 2 minutes on high speed.
Pour into sherbet or wine glasses.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine oil and flour in heavy pot and cook slowly, stirring often to make a medium brown roux.
This will take 1/2 hour or more, but do not raise temperature, as it will burn easily.
If it develops black specks, it is best not to continue as it looses its consistency if it burns.
When roux is color desired, add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic and saute until veggies are wilted. Add tomato sauce and diced tomatoes and blend well.
Slowly add shellfish stock and wine, a little at a time, until smooth.
Allow to simmer until thick.
Add more stock, if needed.
Add green onions and parsley about 15 minutes before mixture is done.
Add shrimp and cook just until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice.
Add a drop or two of Tabasco, if desired.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, and mix well.
Store mix in an airtight container.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients like cake batter and put in a buttered 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix sugar and cherries well.
Put on top of batter.
Pour boiling water over top of cherries.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender; drain.
Add carrots, cut up onion and pepper.
Marinate overnight.

title: microwave chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Make sandwiches with the crackers and peanut butter.
Melt a square or two of the chocolate bark in the microwave.
Dip the sandwiches (using tongs) in the hot chocolate.
Place on wax paper. Let dry thoroughly.
(You can also place in the freezer to speed dry.)

title: red velvet cake
directions: In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs with fork; add vegetable oil.
Beat again, using mixer.
Add buttermilk, food coloring, vinegar, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until smooth.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients and heat with mixture until well blended.
Pour into 4 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool before frosting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter and flour in pan and blend.
Add vegetables and seasoning.
Cool 5 minutes; pour over squash and cover with bread crumbs, cheese and 1 tablespoon oleo (melted).
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Beat egg; add milk, then the dry ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until as thick as desired.
Add vanilla.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: cathy's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together. Store in large airtight container. Use about 1/4 cup dry mixture per mug of hot water. One recipe of this lasts about 1 winter and is fast to fix when coming inside from cold weather. It's also very creamy.

title: skillet barbecue
directions: Cook onions in oleo until tender, but not brown.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer uncovered about 15 minutes, until thickened.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add food coloring and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add salt, flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vanilla; do not beat hard.
Hand mix just to blend. Bake at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt Parkay in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl, approximately 1 minute.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave 5 minutes, stir well after 3 minutes and then stir after the remaining 2 minutes. Microwave an additional 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir well after 3 minutes and then stir after the remaining 2 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips. Mix well until the mixture is creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Makes about 4 pounds of fudge.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix dry cake mix and 1 egg.
Pat in pan over margarine.
Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar until light and smooth.
Spread over cake mix. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and then cut in squares.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water.
Drain and return to saucepan.
Pour melted butter over it.
Mix grated cheese with the spaghetti.
Cut bacon or sausages into small pieces; add to spaghetti and cheese.
(If sausages are too dry and hard, put them through a meat grinder.) Add cracker meal, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Beat eggs.
Add to mixture; mix well.

title: all-purpose refrigerator dough(bread and rolls)
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and baking powder.
Add shortening and use pastry as for pie crust.
Add yeast mixed in lukewarm water and thoroughly dissolved according to package directions.
Add buttermilk and knead with hands until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Put dough in bowl, cover tightly to avoid drying out and set in refrigerator until ready to use.

Dough can be used at once, but it is better if left in refrigerator overnight or until well chilled before handling. Properly stored in refrigerator, dough remains fresh 8 to 10 days; keeps a month in freezer.

title: one pan meal
directions: Arrange ingredients by layer.
Pour reserved bean juice over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: In medium saucepan, place celery, onions, thyme, nutmeg, black pepper and chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender (about 15 minutes).

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter 1 minute. Remove from heat and add chips and vanilla. Beat well into spreading consistency. Makes enough for 9 x 13 cake or top, middle and sides of an 8-inch 2-layer cake. Delicious and quick.

title: barbecue hamburger mix
directions: Saute onion and ground beef until beef is browned.
Drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: sea scallops with lime butter
directions: Cut limes into quarters.
Alternately place 3 scallops and 2 lime wedges on each skewer.
Combine melted butter and lime juice. Grill over a medium-high flame for 3 to 4 minutes, basting frequently.

title: date roll
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and moisten with half and half until mixture forms a roll and is not crumbly.
Roll in waxed paper. Chill for at least 24 hours.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (save some Cool Whip for top) and pour into baked pie crusts.
Chill 4 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bully pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dates and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Spoon into dishes and serve with Cool Whip.

title: gnocchi (potato pasta)
directions: Combine water, milk, salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Add buds or flakes.
Let mixture cool enough so you can work in flour with hands.
Knead until all flour is worked into potato mixture.
Cut pieces, to roll, into 12 "ropes".
Using a butter knife cut pasta into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Indent pasta with index finger (optional).
To cook:
Bring large pot of water to boil and 1/2 teaspoon salt if desired.
Add pasta to water, when gnocchi dumplings rise to top approximately 8 to 10 minutes, drain. Cover with favorite tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sunflower salad dressing
directions: Add to mixer in given order at medium speed.
Stir in sunflower seeds just before serving.

title: fresh cabin apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs and oil together in a large bowl. Combine sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and flour together in small bowl and then gradually add to egg mixture. Add apples, nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixing by hand. Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 60 to 70 minutes or until done when toothpick is inserted in middle.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Mix everything except chocolate chips and nuts together.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add chips and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Frost with vanilla or chocolate frosting when cool.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Fill with apples.
Fold over and pinch edges together.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over apple dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat all ingredients, except popcorn, to boiling in Dutch oven over medium to high heat, stirring constantly. Add popcorn. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring constantly until popcorn is well coated. Cool slightly. Dip hands into cold water; shape mixture into 2 1/2-inch balls. Place on waxed paper and cool. Wrap individually in plastic bags and seal.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: raw potato meat balls
directions: Mix all together to make meat balls.
Boil 1 inch water in pan; add meat balls in water and simmer.
Can make gravy to taste.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in sugar-cinnamon mix (1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon).
Pile in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: simply delicious and easy apple cake
directions: Mix box cake mix according to directions on package. Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg. If you really like cinnamon, add a lot. Batter will turn light brown. Pour into a 13 x 9 inch well greased cake pan (I spray mine with Pam). Peel and cut into chunks at least 4 large apples. Insert them into cake by just laying them on top. I put lots and lots of apples into the cake. Then with a knife I push them down so that the batter comes up above them. Sprinkle a little more cinnamon and nutmeg on top of the cake and bake according to directions on the cake mix box. Serve warm with a scoop of ice cream on top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and molasses; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Form into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie(you may use fresh peaches, soft and ripe, and peach jello)
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of cornstarch. Bring 1 3/4 cups water to a boil.
Add sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until clear.
Add jello.
Let this cool slightly before adding sliced fruit.
Cool and pour into pie crust.
Place in refrigerator a few hours to set up. Top with Cool Whip or just serve a large spoonful of Cool Whip with each slice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan.
Slice sugar cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices. Spread over pan and press together.
Bake according to dough directions.
Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese, lemon and cream. Spread over baked crust.
Blend apple jelly, orange juice and cornstarch over low heat.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.
Glaze with apple jelly mixture.
Allow glaze to cool. Refrigerate.
Cut with pizza cutter.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and hollow out potatoes, saving skins. Beat inner part of potatoes and add other ingredients, beating well. Re-stuff potatoes and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: deedie's congealed asparagus salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Add salt, sugar or Equal, boiling water and vinegar.
Cook on low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into container and put in fridge to congeal.
Serve on lettuce and top with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: easy 15 bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Next morning, empty Ro-Tel into crock-pot along with rinsed beans.
Add enough water to cover beans, flavor packet from bean package and lemon juice.
Cook on high for 6 hours, then turn on low for 4 hours.
Add chili powder the last hour.
Serve with Mexican cornbread and salad.

title: fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large pan and stir over low heat until dissolved.
Turn up heat, stir a few times until it comes to a boil.
Cover and let boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add chocolate and stir until melted.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 15-inch pan and chill before cutting.

title: chicken squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, soup and egg together.
Stir into vegetables and chicken.
Place layer of bread crumbs or stuffing in baking dish.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Top with remaining bread crumbs or stuffing. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan generously.
Add all ingredients, one at a time, on top of each other, beginning with pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Chop the beef very fine; also mushrooms and olives.
Soften cream cheese and add all ingredients.
Roll into ball. Serve with crackers, Sociables.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat vanilla and eggs 3 minutes. Stir together butter, brown sugar and white sugar. Put together with egg mixture. Add flour, soda and salt. Mixture will be sticky and dry. Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by spoon on waxed paper; form into balls on a cookie sheet. Always use new waxed paper. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes and cool 3 to 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix beef broth, tomato juice, lemon juice, chopped onion, sliced garlic, Tabasco, salt and pepper and chill 4 hours. Meanwhile, chop green pepper, cucumber and tomato; chill.
Divide vegetables into soup bowl.
Pour soup over vegetables.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sparkling rainbow melon
directions: In large, nonmetal bowl, combine all ingredients, except carbonated beverage.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat oven to 350°. Mix batter and pour over butter. Bake 30 minutes or longer if needed. For browner top, place under broiler for a few seconds. Best served warm.

title: cheesecake surprise
directions: Layer 1 package rolls, cheese mixture, then second package of rolls.
Brush egg white on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zesty deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half lengthwise.
Place yolks in a bowl. Stir in next 8 ingredients.
Transfer yolk mixture to pastry bag and pipe into eggs white halves.
Can spoon in carefully.
Before serving sprinkle with paprika. Top each egg half with parsley leaf if desired.

title: prize winning chocolate praline cake
directions: In a saucepan add oleo, milk and brown sugar.
Cook until oleo melts.
Pour into two 8 x 10-inch cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans over mixture.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook shrimp and green pepper with garlic and red pepper until shrimp turn pink. Stir in soup and water.
Heat thoroughly and serve over fettucine. (Recipe can be doubled.)

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in bowl.
Mix all other ingredients and marinate chicken for at least 6 hours.
Barbecue marinated chicken until done.
Heat sauce in microwave until hot.
Place chicken back in sauce and serve.
Excellent.

title: fruit salad(myrtle mclean's)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Very good!

title: chicken patty
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together first 8 ingredients; spread in pan.
Top with Cheddar and crushed potato chips.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes; uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat all but nuts for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over nuts in bottom of a greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: day before payday cake
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Then add the last four ingredients.
Stir until mixed, then beat 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350 for 35-45 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter until meat loses pink color and onions are tender.
Add mushrooms, flour and salt to taste. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off flame and add soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat.
Serve over medium size egg noodles until tender.

title: pineapple coconut tartlets
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Cut 5 to 6 (3 3/4 to 4-inch) circles from each pie crust using biscuit cutters.
Place circles on cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Mix egg and water.
Brush edge of dough with egg mixture. Place 1 tablespoon pineapple filling in center.
Fold edges, overlapping dough to make pleats.
Brush outer edge with egg mixture.
Sprinkle edge with additional sugar.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool; dollop with jam.
Serves 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Sift all dry ingredients and mix with sugar mixture. Add carrots and nuts. Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 325°.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut tenderloin across the grain into 1/4-inch strips about 2 inches long.
In large skillet brown meat in oil.
Stir in beef, sugar and soy sauce.
Place mushrooms, green onions, onion, celery and bamboo shoots in skillet.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add frozen vegetables and sliced water chestnuts until heated through.
Do not overcook.
Vegetables should still be crisp and bright in color.

title: party fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Add a little milk for creaminess.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shred lettuce over bottom; chop spinach over top of lettuce.
Next, add chopped green onions, peas, eggs and bacon.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing.
Spread over the top of pan.
Make 24 hours in advance of serving.
Serves 12.

title: stir-fried pork with chinese cabbage and buckwheat noodles
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook noodles until tender but still firm, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse briefly under cold running water; drain well.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix ingredients together until well coated.
Chill and serve.

title: no-bake peanut oatmeal drops
directions: Mix sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in last 4 ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until set.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: classic rice pilaf(serves 4)
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft.
Stir in rice and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until rice is lightly browned. Pour in chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer until rice is tender (about 25 minutes).
Stir once or twice and season to taste with salt.
Toss gently with cheese.

title: 3 bean salad(diabetic)
directions: Mix
and chill. Drain before serving. Excellent.

title: green angel
directions: Cook angel hair pasta in boiling water until done.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup water.
Mix angel hair pasta, defrosted spinach souffle and reserved water.
When serving, sprinkle on Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: incredible egg macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner according to package directions. Add peas, tomato, salad dressing, celery, onion and seasonings. Chop five eggs; add to dinner mixture. Mix lightly. Chill.
Stir in additional salad dressing before serving. Garnish with remaining egg, sliced.

title: apple ring pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers, cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds with spoon and slice crosswise.
On first day, peel, seed, slice and soak 24 hours in lime and water.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies in a Ziploc storage food bag with a rolling pan. Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into plastic 7-ounce cups.
Then fill cups up 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Plant gummy worms into the cups of dirt.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: rosemary game hen
directions: Brown hens in oil.
Add garlic.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Add 1/2 cup water or chicken stock.
Cover; reduce heat to low and cook until done, 40 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook oil and flour over medium heat to make a roux.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are wilted.
Add canned mushrooms.
Add chicken breasts and saute for 10 minutes.
Slowly add chicken stock. Stir.
Bring to a rolling boil, reduce to simmer, and cook about 1 hour.
You may need to add more chicken stock to retain liquid. Add green onions, parsley, Tony's seasoning, salt and pepper. Cook 30 more minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry lemon slush
directions: Put 1 cup water, lemon juice, sugar and 2 cups strawberries in blender; adjust lid.
Blend until strawberries are pureed and sugar is completely dissolved.
In pitcher, combine strawberry mixture with remaining 2 cups water and few drops red food coloring.
Mix well.
Add crushed ice, sliced strawberries and lemon slice floaters to strawberry mixture in pitcher.
Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Cook 3 minutes and knead.
Makes nice, soft play dough.
Store in Tupperware.
Will last for a long time and doesn't stain.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook until onions are glossy, then add ketchup.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place beets, vinegar, salt, sugar and water into saucepan; heat just until sugar dissolves. Place eggs into a 1/2 gallon jar. Add beet mixture. Make sure all eggs are covered. If not, add enough water to cover. Refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg; beat well. Sift together flour, baking soda, allspice, cinnamon and salt. Add to shortening mixture; stir in pears and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand until cool.
Remove from pan.

title: peanut dip(dairyless dip)
directions: Combine peanut butter with oil and whisk; add rest of ingredients.
Serve with vegetable sticks.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown and crumble bacon, drain on paper towel.
Toast sesame seeds and almonds at 350° for 5 minutes (watch closely, almonds burn easily).
Break lettuce into bite size pieces, add onions. Top with bacon, seeds, almonds and noodles.

title: kraut recipe
directions: Cut cabbage and pack into quart jars.
Add to each quart, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar, then to each quart add 1 tablespoon of white vinegar.
Fill jars with water and seal.

title: cheesy chicken & rice
directions: Cook cubed chicken in butter w/garlic salt until done. Stir in vegetables and chicken broth. Cook for 1 minute after it starts to boil. Pour in the 2 c. rice and add cheese cubes, stirring until the cheese melts (it will thicken as it sets).

title: potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, carrots and celery until tender in a large pot.
Drain; keep liquid. Add onion and butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Add remaining vegetable liquid to desired consistency.

title: pineapple-melon slush
directions: Whirl together pineapple and cantaloupe in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Serve cold.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and drop into 1/8 inch of hot oil.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla extract in a double boiler; mix thoroughly.
Cook, beating constantly with rotary or electric mixer until mixture forms peaks, about seven minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in one bowl.
In a second bowl, blend eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda.
In a saucepan, mix margarine, cocoa, oil and water and bring to a boil.
Blend all 3 mixtures together.
Pour in ungreased baking dish (1/2 inch deep). and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large baking dish or bowl.
Top with 1/2 pound fried bacon, crumbled, and 1/2 cup chopped olives (optional).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: elaine's cauliflower salad
directions: Toss vegetables and dressing.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Toss again when ready to serve.

title: coca-cola beef roast
directions: Put roast in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle soup over meat.
Pour Coke over top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: blender pie
directions: Blend for 1 minute in the blender.
Pour in a well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: passion salad(strawberry filling for mini pie shells)
directions: Cream together cream cheese, condensed milk and vanilla instant pudding. Add Cool Whip and beat until smooth. Fold in strawberry pie filling. Can be spooned into pastry shells and chilled.

title: wigglers
directions: Fry bacon and remove from skillet. Fry hamburger and onion in bacon grease.
Put in a roaster and add rest of ingredients. Arrange bacon on top.
Add cheese and tomato juice or soup.
Bake in moderate oven 1 1/2 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with pecans and coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix butter, cheese and sugar; pour over batter.
Put Angel Flake coconut on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: bacon tomato dip
directions: In medium bowl stir together all ingredients until well mixed. Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve dip with crackers, chips or cut-up fresh vegetables.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Melt
margarine
and
add brown sugar and beat together for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients. Spread
on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maggie's apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except marshmallows; put them in last.
Refrigerate.

title: mom's sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients together over low to medium heat until thick (use heavy pan).
Stir constantly.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites for meringue.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Break lettuce and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add chopped onion.
In separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Stir all together.
Seal and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: dream cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Blend cream cheese mixture and whipped cream together.
Tear 1/2 angel food cake into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Cover with whipped cream mixture.
Cover with another layer of cake and whipped cream mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Saute onion.
Add mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and add to softened (not melted) butter.
Cut rolls horizontally and spread mixture on bottom half of rolls. Layer diced ham and cheese on top of mixture.
Replace tops of rolls and wrap in foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and remove from pan.
Drain off all but 2 T grease from pan. Chop mushroom stems finely and brown with onions and garlic in grease until onions just start turning golden; drain and remove from pan.

title: cough syrup
directions: Give 1 teaspoon as needed.

title: tuna bake
directions: Use 8 x 8 pan. In bowl, mix 2 eggs, milk, mustard and paprika; set aside. Grease bottom of pan. Put 4 slices of bread down to cover bottom of pan. Next put tuna on bread, cheese on tuna and remaining 4 slices of bread on top. Pour egg mixture over all. Let sit 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix first ten ingredients together in saucepan and cook until thickened.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix sauce together with chicken and spaghetti in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
The last ten minutes, sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Sift flour sugar together.
Heat butter, marshmallows, cocoa and coca cola together stirring until melted and smooth.
Add to flour and sugar, mix immediately.
Add eggs, mix well, add soda, milk and vanilla, mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in 3 9 inch layers or 1 sheet cake pan.
Bake 40 min. in 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; debone and cut into small pieces. Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a casserole dish.
Then put in 1/2 of chicken.
Mix the can of celery soup with 1 can of broth from the cooked chicken, and pour over chicken.
Put remainder of chicken next.
Mix chicken soup with one can of broth and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 layers from cake mix.
Place 7 ingredients in punch bowl layered as written.
Make 2 layers.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Serves large group of 40 to 50.

title: mints
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar like pie dough.
Add flavoring.
Put the sugar on waxed paper; lay mixture out on waxed paper.
Let dry for 4 to 5 days.
Make into shapes, such as rose, leaf and Christmas tree.

title: x-tra mashed potatoes
directions: Mix your own mashed potatoes with cream cheese, onion and pimento.
Bake in casserole at 350° until golden on top.

title: broccoli-rice quiche
directions: Bring water to boil in a saucepan.
Add broccoli and onion; cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup egg substitute and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Press evenly over bottoms and up sides of two 9-inch pie plates coated with cooking spray.
Combine 1 cup egg substitute, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, milk, mushrooms and broccoli mixture in a bowl; stir well.
Pour evenly into prepared dishes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese; bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
12 servings (145 calories and 19% fat per serving).

title: frosted mint delight
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Soften gelatin in pineapple syrup.
Add mint jelly.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved and jelly melts.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill approximately 20 minutes.
Whip the cream and sugar until stiff. Fold in pineapple mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature until serving consistency.
Serves 12.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In microwave safe dish, stir together everything but eggs. Cover.
Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Stir twice before boiling. Stir in swirling motion and slowly pour eggs in broth until they become long strands.

title: kerry's yorkshire chicken
directions: Combine 1/3 cup flour, 2 teaspoons salt, sage and pepper in a plastic bag.
Shake chicken in bag to coat with mixture.
Brown chicken in oil and transfer to baking dish.
Sift remaining flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix milk, butter and beaten eggs.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add parsley.
Pour batter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and oats.
Mix in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for 15 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from range and add peanut butter, mix well.
Add cornflakes and coconut.
Mix well and drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: taco beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Wash.
Add taco mix.
Cook 30 minutes fast, then lower heat. Add green chilies, tomato sauce and onion. Cook very slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, add butter.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook turkey breast and chop up.
Cut grapes in half.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add to this enough pineapple and cherry juice to make another cup of liquid.
(I drain my fruit overnight.)
Refrigerate until consistency of gravy.
Add fruit, nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip; mix thoroughly and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn fritters
directions: In frying pan, add oil and heat to 350°.
In bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, egg, milk and corn.
Drop tablespoonful in hot oil until brown.

title: hot slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Dice onion and mix with cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry bacon; drain and reserve bacon grease.
Add 1 cup of sugar and vinegar to bacon grease and heat to boiling. Taste to see if sweet enough.
Pour over cabbage while hot and mix.
Sprinkle with fried bacon.

title: pork hocks and sauerkraut
directions: Boil hocks until bones come to top and foamy.
Change water and put hocks in.
Boil and add bay leaf, onion, whole cloves. Cook until hocks are soft; put with potatoes.
Season to taste after adding drained sauerkraut and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 Tbsp. butter.
Stir in flour and add water. Stir until thickened.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli; pour eggs over all.
Turn into greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Saute croutons in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: super cole slaw
directions: Place ingredients in large bowl, in order given.
Mix well. Cover; chill thoroughly.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk; mix until well blended.
Grease a 9-inch pan and pour batter into pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar. Sprinkle over cake batter and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
